46 M68kTargetLowering::M68kTargetLowering(const M68kTargetMachine &TM,
47  const M68kSubtarget &STI)
48  : TargetLowering(TM), Subtarget(STI), TM(TM) {
49 
50  MVT PtrVT = MVT::i32;
51 
52  setBooleanContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
53 
54  auto *RegInfo = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
55  setStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(RegInfo->getStackRegister());
56 
57  // Set up the register classes.
58  addRegisterClass(MVT::i8, &M68k::DR8RegClass);
59  addRegisterClass(MVT::i16, &M68k::XR16RegClass);
60  addRegisterClass(MVT::i32, &M68k::XR32RegClass);
61 
62  for (auto VT : MVT::integer_valuetypes()) {
63  setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
64  setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
65  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
66  }
67 
68  // We don't accept any truncstore of integer registers.
69  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i64, MVT::i32, Expand);
70  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i64, MVT::i16, Expand);
71  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i64, MVT::i8, Expand);
72  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i32, MVT::i16, Expand);
73  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i32, MVT::i8, Expand);
74  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i16, MVT::i8, Expand);
75 
76  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i8, Promote);
77  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i16, Legal);
78  if (Subtarget.atLeastM68020())
79  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i32, Legal);
80  else
81  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i32, LibCall);
82  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i64, LibCall);
83 
84  for (auto OP :
85  {ISD::SDIV, ISD::UDIV, ISD::SREM, ISD::UREM, ISD::UDIVREM, ISD::SDIVREM,
86  ISD::MULHS, ISD::MULHU, ISD::UMUL_LOHI, ISD::SMUL_LOHI}) {
87  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i8, Promote);
88  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i16, Legal);
89  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i32, LibCall);
90  }
91 
92  for (auto OP : {ISD::UMUL_LOHI, ISD::SMUL_LOHI}) {
93  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i8, Expand);
94  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i16, Expand);
95  }
96 
97  // FIXME It would be better to use a custom lowering
98  for (auto OP : {ISD::SMULO, ISD::UMULO}) {
99  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i8, Expand);
100  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i16, Expand);
101  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i32, Expand);
102  }
103 
104  for (auto OP : {ISD::SHL_PARTS, ISD::SRA_PARTS, ISD::SRL_PARTS})
105  setOperationAction(OP, MVT::i32, Custom);
106 
107  // Add/Sub overflow ops with MVT::Glues are lowered to CCR dependences.
108  for (auto VT : {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}) {
109  setOperationAction(ISD::ADDC, VT, Custom);
110  setOperationAction(ISD::ADDE, VT, Custom);
111  setOperationAction(ISD::SUBC, VT, Custom);
112  setOperationAction(ISD::SUBE, VT, Custom);
113  }
114 
115  // SADDO and friends are legal with this setup, i hope
116  for (auto VT : {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}) {
117  setOperationAction(ISD::SADDO, VT, Custom);
118  setOperationAction(ISD::UADDO, VT, Custom);
119  setOperationAction(ISD::SSUBO, VT, Custom);
120  setOperationAction(ISD::USUBO, VT, Custom);
121  }
122 
123  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_JT, MVT::Other, Expand);
124  setOperationAction(ISD::BRCOND, MVT::Other, Custom);
125 
126  for (auto VT : {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}) {
127  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, VT, Expand);
128  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, VT, Custom);
129  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, VT, Expand);
130  setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, VT, Custom);
131  setOperationAction(ISD::SETCCCARRY, VT, Custom);
132  }
133 
134  for (auto VT : {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}) {
135  setOperationAction(ISD::BSWAP, VT, Expand);
136  setOperationAction(ISD::CTTZ, VT, Expand);
137  setOperationAction(ISD::CTLZ, VT, Expand);
138  setOperationAction(ISD::CTPOP, VT, Expand);
139  }
140 
141  setOperationAction(ISD::ConstantPool, MVT::i32, Custom);
142  setOperationAction(ISD::JumpTable, MVT::i32, Custom);
143  setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
144  setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
145  setOperationAction(ISD::ExternalSymbol, MVT::i32, Custom);
146  setOperationAction(ISD::BlockAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
147 
148  setOperationAction(ISD::VASTART, MVT::Other, Custom);
149  setOperationAction(ISD::VAEND, MVT::Other, Expand);
150  setOperationAction(ISD::VAARG, MVT::Other, Expand);
151  setOperationAction(ISD::VACOPY, MVT::Other, Expand);
152 
153  setOperationAction(ISD::STACKSAVE, MVT::Other, Expand);
154  setOperationAction(ISD::STACKRESTORE, MVT::Other, Expand);
155 
156  setOperationAction(ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC, PtrVT, Custom);
157 
158  computeRegisterProperties(STI.getRegisterInfo());
159 
160  // We lower the `atomic-compare-and-swap` to `__sync_val_compare_and_swap`
161  // for subtarget < M68020
162  setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(32);
163  setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32},
164  Subtarget.atLeastM68020() ? Legal : LibCall);
165 
166  // M68k does not have native read-modify-write support, so expand all of them
167  // to `__sync_fetch_*` for target < M68020, otherwise expand to CmpxChg.
168  // See `shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR` below.
169  setOperationAction(
170  {
171  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD,
172  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB,
173  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND,
174  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR,
175  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR,
176  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND,
177  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN,
178  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX,
179  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN,
180  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX,
181  },
182  {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}, LibCall);
183 
184  setMinFunctionAlignment(Align(2));
185 }

210 enum StructReturnType { NotStructReturn, RegStructReturn, StackStructReturn };
211 
212 static StructReturnType
213 callIsStructReturn(const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs) {
214  if (Outs.empty())
215  return NotStructReturn;
216 
217  const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags = Outs[0].Flags;
218  if (!Flags.isSRet())
219  return NotStructReturn;
220  if (Flags.isInReg())
221  return RegStructReturn;
222  return StackStructReturn;
223 }
224 
225 /// Determines whether a function uses struct return semantics.
226 static StructReturnType
227 argsAreStructReturn(const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins) {
228  if (Ins.empty())
229  return NotStructReturn;
230 
231  const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags = Ins[0].Flags;
232  if (!Flags.isSRet())
233  return NotStructReturn;
234  if (Flags.isInReg())
235  return RegStructReturn;
236  return StackStructReturn;
237 }

239 /// Make a copy of an aggregate at address specified by "Src" to address
240 /// "Dst" with size and alignment information specified by the specific
241 /// parameter attribute. The copy will be passed as a byval function parameter.
242 static SDValue CreateCopyOfByValArgument(SDValue Src, SDValue Dst,
243  SDValue Chain, ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags,
244  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL) {
245  SDValue SizeNode = DAG.getConstant(Flags.getByValSize(), DL, MVT::i32);
246 
247  return DAG.getMemcpy(
248  Chain, DL, Dst, Src, SizeNode, Flags.getNonZeroByValAlign(),
249  /*isVolatile=*/false, /*AlwaysInline=*/true,
250  /*isTailCall=*/false, MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
251 }

253 /// Return true if the calling convention is one that we can guarantee TCO for.
254 static bool canGuaranteeTCO(CallingConv::ID CC) { return false; }
255 
256 /// Return true if we might ever do TCO for calls with this calling convention.
257 static bool mayTailCallThisCC(CallingConv::ID CC) {
258  switch (CC) {
259  // C calling conventions:
260  case CallingConv::C:
261  return true;
262  default:
263  return canGuaranteeTCO(CC);
264  }
265 }

267 /// Return true if the function is being made into a tailcall target by
268 /// changing its ABI.
269 static bool shouldGuaranteeTCO(CallingConv::ID CC, bool GuaranteedTailCallOpt) {
270  return GuaranteedTailCallOpt && canGuaranteeTCO(CC);
271 }

273 /// Return true if the given stack call argument is already available in the
274 /// same position (relatively) of the caller's incoming argument stack.
275 static bool MatchingStackOffset(SDValue Arg, unsigned Offset,
276  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags, MachineFrameInfo &MFI,
277  const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI,
278  const M68kInstrInfo *TII,
279  const CCValAssign &VA) {
280  unsigned Bytes = Arg.getValueType().getSizeInBits() / 8;
281 
282  for (;;) {
283  // Look through nodes that don't alter the bits of the incoming value.
284  unsigned Op = Arg.getOpcode();
285  if (Op == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || Op == ISD::ANY_EXTEND || Op == ISD::BITCAST) {
286  Arg = Arg.getOperand(0);
287  continue;
288  }
289  if (Op == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
290  const SDValue &TruncInput = Arg.getOperand(0);
291  if (TruncInput.getOpcode() == ISD::AssertZext &&
292  cast<VTSDNode>(TruncInput.getOperand(1))->getVT() ==
293  Arg.getValueType()) {
294  Arg = TruncInput.getOperand(0);
295  continue;
296  }
297  }
298  break;
299  }
300 
301  int FI = INT_MAX;
302  if (Arg.getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg) {
303  Register VR = cast<RegisterSDNode>(Arg.getOperand(1))->getReg();
304  if (!Register::isVirtualRegister(VR))
305  return false;
306  MachineInstr *Def = MRI->getVRegDef(VR);
307  if (!Def)
308  return false;
309  if (!Flags.isByVal()) {
310  if (!TII->isLoadFromStackSlot(*Def, FI))
311  return false;
312  } else {
313  unsigned Opcode = Def->getOpcode();
314  if ((Opcode == M68k::LEA32p || Opcode == M68k::LEA32f) &&
315  Def->getOperand(1).isFI()) {
316  FI = Def->getOperand(1).getIndex();
317  Bytes = Flags.getByValSize();
318  } else
319  return false;
320  }
321  } else if (auto *Ld = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(Arg)) {
322  if (Flags.isByVal())
323  // ByVal argument is passed in as a pointer but it's now being
324  // dereferenced. e.g.
325  // define @foo(%struct.X* %A) {
326  // tail call @bar(%struct.X* byval %A)
327  // }
328  return false;
329  SDValue Ptr = Ld->getBasePtr();
330  FrameIndexSDNode *FINode = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr);
331  if (!FINode)
332  return false;
333  FI = FINode->getIndex();
334  } else if (Arg.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex && Flags.isByVal()) {
335  FrameIndexSDNode *FINode = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Arg);
336  FI = FINode->getIndex();
337  Bytes = Flags.getByValSize();
338  } else
339  return false;
340 
341  assert(FI != INT_MAX);
342  if (!MFI.isFixedObjectIndex(FI))
343  return false;
344 
345  if (Offset != MFI.getObjectOffset(FI))
346  return false;
347 
348  if (VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits() > Arg.getValueType().getSizeInBits()) {
349  // If the argument location is wider than the argument type, check that any
350  // extension flags match.
351  if (Flags.isZExt() != MFI.isObjectZExt(FI) ||
352  Flags.isSExt() != MFI.isObjectSExt(FI)) {
353  return false;
354  }
355  }
356 
357  return Bytes == MFI.getObjectSize(FI);
358 }

360 SDValue
361 M68kTargetLowering::getReturnAddressFrameIndex(SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
362  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
363  M68kMachineFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<M68kMachineFunctionInfo>();
364  int ReturnAddrIndex = FuncInfo->getRAIndex();
365 
366  if (ReturnAddrIndex == 0) {
367  // Set up a frame object for the return address.
368  unsigned SlotSize = Subtarget.getSlotSize();
369  ReturnAddrIndex = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(
370  SlotSize, -(int64_t)SlotSize, false);
371  FuncInfo->setRAIndex(ReturnAddrIndex);
372  }
373 
374  return DAG.getFrameIndex(ReturnAddrIndex, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
375 }

377 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::EmitTailCallLoadRetAddr(SelectionDAG &DAG,
378  SDValue &OutRetAddr,
379  SDValue Chain,
380  bool IsTailCall, int FPDiff,
381  const SDLoc &DL) const {
382  EVT VT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
383  OutRetAddr = getReturnAddressFrameIndex(DAG);
384 
385  // Load the "old" Return address.
386  OutRetAddr = DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, Chain, OutRetAddr, MachinePointerInfo());
387  return SDValue(OutRetAddr.getNode(), 1);
388 }

390 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::EmitTailCallStoreRetAddr(
391  SelectionDAG &DAG, MachineFunction &MF, SDValue Chain, SDValue RetFI,
392  EVT PtrVT, unsigned SlotSize, int FPDiff, const SDLoc &DL) const {
393  if (!FPDiff)
394  return Chain;
395 
396  // Calculate the new stack slot for the return address.
397  int NewFO = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(
398  SlotSize, (int64_t)FPDiff - SlotSize, false);
399 
400  SDValue NewFI = DAG.getFrameIndex(NewFO, PtrVT);
401  // Store the return address to the appropriate stack slot.
402  Chain = DAG.getStore(
403  Chain, DL, RetFI, NewFI,
404  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), NewFO));
405  return Chain;
406 }

408 SDValue
409 M68kTargetLowering::LowerMemArgument(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
410  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins,
411  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
412  const CCValAssign &VA,
413  MachineFrameInfo &MFI,
414  unsigned ArgIdx) const {
415  // Create the nodes corresponding to a load from this parameter slot.
416  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Ins[ArgIdx].Flags;
417  EVT ValVT;
418 
419  // If value is passed by pointer we have address passed instead of the value
420  // itself.
421  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
422  ValVT = VA.getLocVT();
423  else
424  ValVT = VA.getValVT();
425 
426  // Because we are dealing with BE architecture we need to offset loading of
427  // partial types
428  int Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset();
429  if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i8) {
430  Offset += 3;
431  } else if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i16) {
432  Offset += 2;
433  }
434 
435  // TODO Interrupt handlers
436  // Calculate SP offset of interrupt parameter, re-arrange the slot normally
437  // taken by a return address.
438 
439  // FIXME For now, all byval parameter objects are marked mutable. This can
440  // be changed with more analysis. In case of tail call optimization mark all
441  // arguments mutable. Since they could be overwritten by lowering of arguments
442  // in case of a tail call.
443  bool AlwaysUseMutable = shouldGuaranteeTCO(
444  CallConv, DAG.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt);
445  bool IsImmutable = !AlwaysUseMutable && !Flags.isByVal();
446 
447  if (Flags.isByVal()) {
448  unsigned Bytes = Flags.getByValSize();
449  if (Bytes == 0)
450  Bytes = 1; // Don't create zero-sized stack objects.
451  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(Bytes, Offset, IsImmutable);
452  // TODO Interrupt handlers
453  // Adjust SP offset of interrupt parameter.
454  return DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
455  } else {
456  int FI =
457  MFI.CreateFixedObject(ValVT.getSizeInBits() / 8, Offset, IsImmutable);
458 
459  // Set SExt or ZExt flag.
460  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExt) {
461  MFI.setObjectZExt(FI, true);
462  } else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::SExt) {
463  MFI.setObjectSExt(FI, true);
464  }
465 
466  // TODO Interrupt handlers
467  // Adjust SP offset of interrupt parameter.
468 
469  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
470  SDValue Val = DAG.getLoad(
471  ValVT, DL, Chain, FIN,
472  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI));
473  return VA.isExtInLoc() ? DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val)
474  : Val;
475  }
476 }

478 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerMemOpCallTo(SDValue Chain, SDValue StackPtr,
479  SDValue Arg, const SDLoc &DL,
480  SelectionDAG &DAG,
481  const CCValAssign &VA,
482  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags) const {
483  unsigned LocMemOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset();
484  SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(LocMemOffset, DL);
485  PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()),
486  StackPtr, PtrOff);
487  if (Flags.isByVal())
488  return CreateCopyOfByValArgument(Arg, PtrOff, Chain, Flags, DAG, DL);
489 
490  return DAG.getStore(
491  Chain, DL, Arg, PtrOff,
492  MachinePointerInfo::getStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), LocMemOffset));
493 }

499 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerCall(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
500  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
501  SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
502  SDLoc &DL = CLI.DL;
503  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
504  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
505  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
506  SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
507  SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
508  CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
509  bool &IsTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall;
510  bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
511 
512  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
513  StructReturnType SR = callIsStructReturn(Outs);
514  bool IsSibcall = false;
515  M68kMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo<M68kMachineFunctionInfo>();
516  // const M68kRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
517 
518  if (CallConv == CallingConv::M68k_INTR)
519  report_fatal_error("M68k interrupts may not be called directly");
520 
521  auto Attr = MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("disable-tail-calls");
522  if (Attr.getValueAsBool())
523  IsTailCall = false;
524 
525  // FIXME Add tailcalls support
526 
527  bool IsMustTail = CLI.CB && CLI.CB->isMustTailCall();
528  if (IsMustTail) {
529  // Force this to be a tail call. The verifier rules are enough to ensure
530  // that we can lower this successfully without moving the return address
531  // around.
532  IsTailCall = true;
533  } else if (IsTailCall) {
534  // Check if it's really possible to do a tail call.
535  IsTailCall = IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
536  Callee, CallConv, IsVarArg, SR != NotStructReturn,
537  MF.getFunction().hasStructRetAttr(), CLI.RetTy, Outs, OutVals, Ins,
538  DAG);
539 
540  // Sibcalls are automatically detected tailcalls which do not require
541  // ABI changes.
542  if (!MF.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt && IsTailCall)
543  IsSibcall = true;
544 
545  if (IsTailCall)
546  ++NumTailCalls;
547  }
548 
549  assert(!(IsVarArg && canGuaranteeTCO(CallConv)) &&
550  "Var args not supported with calling convention fastcc");
551 
552  // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
553  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
554  SmallVector<Type *, 4> ArgTypes;
555  for (const auto &Arg : CLI.getArgs())
556  ArgTypes.emplace_back(Arg.Ty);
557  M68kCCState CCInfo(ArgTypes, CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs,
558  *DAG.getContext());
559  CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_M68k);
560 
561  // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack.
562  unsigned NumBytes = CCInfo.getAlignedCallFrameSize();
563  if (IsSibcall) {
564  // This is a sibcall. The memory operands are available in caller's
565  // own caller's stack.
566  NumBytes = 0;
567  } else if (MF.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt &&
568  canGuaranteeTCO(CallConv)) {
569  NumBytes = GetAlignedArgumentStackSize(NumBytes, DAG);
570  }
571 
572  int FPDiff = 0;
573  if (IsTailCall && !IsSibcall && !IsMustTail) {
574  // Lower arguments at fp - stackoffset + fpdiff.
575  unsigned NumBytesCallerPushed = MFI->getBytesToPopOnReturn();
576 
577  FPDiff = NumBytesCallerPushed - NumBytes;
578 
579  // Set the delta of movement of the returnaddr stackslot.
580  // But only set if delta is greater than previous delta.
581  if (FPDiff < MFI->getTCReturnAddrDelta())
582  MFI->setTCReturnAddrDelta(FPDiff);
583  }
584 
585  unsigned NumBytesToPush = NumBytes;
586  unsigned NumBytesToPop = NumBytes;
587 
588  // If we have an inalloca argument, all stack space has already been allocated
589  // for us and be right at the top of the stack. We don't support multiple
590  // arguments passed in memory when using inalloca.
591  if (!Outs.empty() && Outs.back().Flags.isInAlloca()) {
592  NumBytesToPush = 0;
593  if (!ArgLocs.back().isMemLoc())
594  report_fatal_error("cannot use inalloca attribute on a register "
595  "parameter");
596  if (ArgLocs.back().getLocMemOffset() != 0)
597  report_fatal_error("any parameter with the inalloca attribute must be "
598  "the only memory argument");
599  }
600 
601  if (!IsSibcall)
602  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, NumBytesToPush,
603  NumBytes - NumBytesToPush, DL);
604 
605  SDValue RetFI;
606  // Load return address for tail calls.
607  if (IsTailCall && FPDiff)
608  Chain = EmitTailCallLoadRetAddr(DAG, RetFI, Chain, IsTailCall, FPDiff, DL);
609 
610  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>, 8> RegsToPass;
611  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
612  SDValue StackPtr;
613 
614  // Walk the register/memloc assignments, inserting copies/loads. In the case
615  // of tail call optimization arguments are handle later.
616  const M68kRegisterInfo *RegInfo = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
617  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
618  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
619 
620  // Skip inalloca arguments, they have already been written.
621  if (Flags.isInAlloca())
622  continue;
623 
624  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
625  EVT RegVT = VA.getLocVT();
626  SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
627  bool IsByVal = Flags.isByVal();
628 
629  // Promote the value if needed.
630  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
631  default:
632  llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
633  case CCValAssign::Full:
634  break;
635  case CCValAssign::SExt:
636  Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, RegVT, Arg);
637  break;
638  case CCValAssign::ZExt:
639  Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, RegVT, Arg);
640  break;
641  case CCValAssign::AExt:
642  Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, RegVT, Arg);
643  break;
644  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
645  Arg = DAG.getBitcast(RegVT, Arg);
646  break;
647  case CCValAssign::Indirect: {
648  // Store the argument.
649  SDValue SpillSlot = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VA.getValVT());
650  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(SpillSlot)->getIndex();
651  Chain = DAG.getStore(
652  Chain, DL, Arg, SpillSlot,
653  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI));
654  Arg = SpillSlot;
655  break;
656  }
657  }
658 
659  if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
660  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg));
661  } else if (!IsSibcall && (!IsTailCall || IsByVal)) {
662  assert(VA.isMemLoc());
663  if (!StackPtr.getNode()) {
664  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RegInfo->getStackRegister(),
665  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
666  }
667  MemOpChains.push_back(
668  LowerMemOpCallTo(Chain, StackPtr, Arg, DL, DAG, VA, Flags));
669  }
670  }
671 
672  if (!MemOpChains.empty())
673  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
674 
675  // FIXME Make sure PIC style GOT works as expected
676  // The only time GOT is really needed is for Medium-PIC static data
677  // otherwise we are happy with pc-rel or static references
678 
679  if (IsVarArg && IsMustTail) {
680  const auto &Forwards = MFI->getForwardedMustTailRegParms();
681  for (const auto &F : Forwards) {
682  SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, F.VReg, F.VT);
683  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(unsigned(F.PReg), Val));
684  }
685  }
686 
687  // For tail calls lower the arguments to the 'real' stack slots. Sibcalls
688  // don't need this because the eligibility check rejects calls that require
689  // shuffling arguments passed in memory.
690  if (!IsSibcall && IsTailCall) {
691  // Force all the incoming stack arguments to be loaded from the stack
692  // before any new outgoing arguments are stored to the stack, because the
693  // outgoing stack slots may alias the incoming argument stack slots, and
694  // the alias isn't otherwise explicit. This is slightly more conservative
695  // than necessary, because it means that each store effectively depends
696  // on every argument instead of just those arguments it would clobber.
697  SDValue ArgChain = DAG.getStackArgumentTokenFactor(Chain);
698 
699  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains2;
700  SDValue FIN;
701  int FI = 0;
702  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
703  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
704  if (VA.isRegLoc())
705  continue;
706  assert(VA.isMemLoc());
707  SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
708  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
709  // Skip inalloca arguments. They don't require any work.
710  if (Flags.isInAlloca())
711  continue;
712  // Create frame index.
713  int32_t Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset() + FPDiff;
714  uint32_t OpSize = (VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits() + 7) / 8;
715  FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(OpSize, Offset, true);
716  FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
717 
718  if (Flags.isByVal()) {
719  // Copy relative to framepointer.
720  SDValue Source = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset(), DL);
721  if (!StackPtr.getNode()) {
722  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RegInfo->getStackRegister(),
723  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
724  }
725  Source = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()),
726  StackPtr, Source);
727 
728  MemOpChains2.push_back(
729  CreateCopyOfByValArgument(Source, FIN, ArgChain, Flags, DAG, DL));
730  } else {
731  // Store relative to framepointer.
732  MemOpChains2.push_back(DAG.getStore(
733  ArgChain, DL, Arg, FIN,
734  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI)));
735  }
736  }
737 
738  if (!MemOpChains2.empty())
739  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains2);
740 
741  // Store the return address to the appropriate stack slot.
742  Chain = EmitTailCallStoreRetAddr(DAG, MF, Chain, RetFI,
743  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()),
744  Subtarget.getSlotSize(), FPDiff, DL);
745  }
746 
747  // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes chained together with token chain
748  // and flag operands which copy the outgoing args into registers.
749  SDValue InFlag;
750  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
751  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RegsToPass[i].first,
752  RegsToPass[i].second, InFlag);
753  InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
754  }
755 
756  if (Callee->getOpcode() == ISD::GlobalAddress) {
757  // If the callee is a GlobalAddress node (quite common, every direct call
758  // is) turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress node so that legalize doesn't hack
759  // it.
760  GlobalAddressSDNode *G = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee);
761 
762  // We should use extra load for direct calls to dllimported functions in
763  // non-JIT mode.
764  const GlobalValue *GV = G->getGlobal();
765  if (!GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass()) {
766  unsigned char OpFlags = Subtarget.classifyGlobalFunctionReference(GV);
767 
768  Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(
769  GV, DL, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), G->getOffset(), OpFlags);
770 
771  if (OpFlags == M68kII::MO_GOTPCREL) {
772 
773  // Add a wrapper.
774  Callee = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::WrapperPC, DL,
775  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), Callee);
776 
777  // Add extra indirection
778  Callee = DAG.getLoad(
779  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), Callee,
780  MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()));
781  }
782  }
783  } else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
784  const Module *Mod = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getParent();
785  unsigned char OpFlags =
786  Subtarget.classifyGlobalFunctionReference(nullptr, *Mod);
787 
788  Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(
789  S->getSymbol(), getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), OpFlags);
790  }
791 
792  // Returns a chain & a flag for retval copy to use.
793  SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
794  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
795 
796  if (!IsSibcall && IsTailCall) {
797  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, NumBytesToPop, 0, InFlag, DL);
798  InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
799  }
800 
801  Ops.push_back(Chain);
802  Ops.push_back(Callee);
803 
804  if (IsTailCall)
805  Ops.push_back(DAG.getConstant(FPDiff, DL, MVT::i32));
806 
807  // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are known live
808  // into the call.
809  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i)
810  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegsToPass[i].first,
811  RegsToPass[i].second.getValueType()));
812 
813  // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
814  const uint32_t *Mask = RegInfo->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallConv);
815  assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
816 
817  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
818 
819  if (InFlag.getNode())
820  Ops.push_back(InFlag);
821 
822  if (IsTailCall) {
823  MF.getFrameInfo().setHasTailCall();
824  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::TC_RETURN, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
825  }
826 
827  Chain = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CALL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
828  InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
829 
830  // Create the CALLSEQ_END node.
831  unsigned NumBytesForCalleeToPop;
832  if (M68k::isCalleePop(CallConv, IsVarArg,
833  DAG.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt)) {
834  NumBytesForCalleeToPop = NumBytes; // Callee pops everything
835  } else if (!canGuaranteeTCO(CallConv) && SR == StackStructReturn) {
836  // If this is a call to a struct-return function, the callee
837  // pops the hidden struct pointer, so we have to push it back.
838  NumBytesForCalleeToPop = 4;
839  } else {
840  NumBytesForCalleeToPop = 0; // Callee pops nothing.
841  }
842 
843  if (CLI.DoesNotReturn && !getTargetMachine().Options.TrapUnreachable) {
844  // No need to reset the stack after the call if the call doesn't return. To
845  // make the MI verify, we'll pretend the callee does it for us.
846  NumBytesForCalleeToPop = NumBytes;
847  }
848 
849  // Returns a flag for retval copy to use.
850  if (!IsSibcall) {
851  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, NumBytesToPop, NumBytesForCalleeToPop,
852  InFlag, DL);
853  InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
854  }
855 
856  // Handle result values, copying them out of physregs into vregs that we
857  // return.
858  return LowerCallResult(Chain, InFlag, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins, DL, DAG,
859  InVals);
860 }
861 
862 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerCallResult(
863  SDValue Chain, SDValue InFlag, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
864  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
865  SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
866 
867  // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
868  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
869  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
870  *DAG.getContext());
871  CCInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_M68k);
872 
873  // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
874  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RVLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
875  CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
876  EVT CopyVT = VA.getLocVT();
877 
878  /// ??? is this correct?
879  Chain = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), CopyVT, InFlag)
880  .getValue(1);
881  SDValue Val = Chain.getValue(0);
882 
883  if (VA.isExtInLoc() && VA.getValVT().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
884  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
885 
886  InFlag = Chain.getValue(2);
887  InVals.push_back(Val);
888  }
889 
890  return Chain;
891 }

893 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
894 // Formal Arguments Calling Convention Implementation
895 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
896 
897 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
898  SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CCID, bool IsVarArg,
899  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
900  SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
901  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
902  M68kMachineFunctionInfo *MMFI = MF.getInfo<M68kMachineFunctionInfo>();
903  // const TargetFrameLowering &TFL = *Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
904 
905  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
906 
907  // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
908  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
909  SmallVector<Type *, 4> ArgTypes;
910  for (const Argument &Arg : MF.getFunction().args())
911  ArgTypes.emplace_back(Arg.getType());
912  M68kCCState CCInfo(ArgTypes, CCID, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext());
913 
914  CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_M68k);
915 
916  unsigned LastVal = ~0U;
917  SDValue ArgValue;
918  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
919  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
920  assert(VA.getValNo() != LastVal && "Same value in different locations");
921 
922  LastVal = VA.getValNo();
923 
924  if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
925  EVT RegVT = VA.getLocVT();
926  const TargetRegisterClass *RC;
927  if (RegVT == MVT::i32)
928  RC = &M68k::XR32RegClass;
929  else
930  llvm_unreachable("Unknown argument type!");
931 
932  Register Reg = MF.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), RC);
933  ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, RegVT);
934 
935  // If this is an 8 or 16-bit value, it is really passed promoted to 32
936  // bits. Insert an assert[sz]ext to capture this, then truncate to the
937  // right size.
938  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::SExt) {
939  ArgValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, DL, RegVT, ArgValue,
940  DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
941  } else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExt) {
942  ArgValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, RegVT, ArgValue,
943  DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
944  } else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::BCvt) {
945  ArgValue = DAG.getBitcast(VA.getValVT(), ArgValue);
946  }
947 
948  if (VA.isExtInLoc()) {
949  ArgValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), ArgValue);
950  }
951  } else {
952  assert(VA.isMemLoc());
953  ArgValue = LowerMemArgument(Chain, CCID, Ins, DL, DAG, VA, MFI, i);
954  }
955 
956  // If value is passed via pointer - do a load.
957  // TODO Make sure this handling on indirect arguments is correct
958  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
959  ArgValue =
960  DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), DL, Chain, ArgValue, MachinePointerInfo());
961 
962  InVals.push_back(ArgValue);
963  }
964 
965  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
966  // Swift calling convention does not require we copy the sret argument
967  // into %D0 for the return. We don't set SRetReturnReg for Swift.
968  if (CCID == CallingConv::Swift)
969  continue;
970 
971  // ABI require that for returning structs by value we copy the sret argument
972  // into %D0 for the return. Save the argument into a virtual register so
973  // that we can access it from the return points.
974  if (Ins[i].Flags.isSRet()) {
975  unsigned Reg = MMFI->getSRetReturnReg();
976  if (!Reg) {
977  MVT PtrTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
978  Reg = MF.getRegInfo().createVirtualRegister(getRegClassFor(PtrTy));
979  MMFI->setSRetReturnReg(Reg);
980  }
981  SDValue Copy = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Reg, InVals[i]);
982  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Copy, Chain);
983  break;
984  }
985  }
986 
987  unsigned StackSize = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
988  // Align stack specially for tail calls.
989  if (shouldGuaranteeTCO(CCID, MF.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt))
990  StackSize = GetAlignedArgumentStackSize(StackSize, DAG);
991 
992  // If the function takes variable number of arguments, make a frame index for
993  // the start of the first vararg value... for expansion of llvm.va_start. We
994  // can skip this if there are no va_start calls.
995  if (MFI.hasVAStart()) {
996  MMFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(MFI.CreateFixedObject(1, StackSize, true));
997  }
998 
999  if (IsVarArg && MFI.hasMustTailInVarArgFunc()) {
1000  // We forward some GPRs and some vector types.
1001  SmallVector<MVT, 2> RegParmTypes;
1002  MVT IntVT = MVT::i32;
1003  RegParmTypes.push_back(IntVT);
1004 
1005  // Compute the set of forwarded registers. The rest are scratch.
1006  // ??? what is this for?
1007  SmallVectorImpl<ForwardedRegister> &Forwards =
1008  MMFI->getForwardedMustTailRegParms();
1009  CCInfo.analyzeMustTailForwardedRegisters(Forwards, RegParmTypes, CC_M68k);
1010 
1011  // Copy all forwards from physical to virtual registers.
1012  for (ForwardedRegister &F : Forwards) {
1013  // FIXME Can we use a less constrained schedule?
1014  SDValue RegVal = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, F.VReg, F.VT);
1015  F.VReg = MF.getRegInfo().createVirtualRegister(getRegClassFor(F.VT));
1016  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, F.VReg, RegVal);
1017  }
1018  }
1019 
1020  // Some CCs need callee pop.
1021  if (M68k::isCalleePop(CCID, IsVarArg,
1022  MF.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt)) {
1023  MMFI->setBytesToPopOnReturn(StackSize); // Callee pops everything.
1024  } else {
1025  MMFI->setBytesToPopOnReturn(0); // Callee pops nothing.
1026  // If this is an sret function, the return should pop the hidden pointer.
1027  if (!canGuaranteeTCO(CCID) && argsAreStructReturn(Ins) == StackStructReturn)
1028  MMFI->setBytesToPopOnReturn(4);
1029  }
1030 
1031  MMFI->setArgumentStackSize(StackSize);
1032 
1033  return Chain;
1034 }
1035 
1036 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1037 // Return Value Calling Convention Implementation
1038 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1039 
1040 SDValue
1041 M68kTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CCID,
1042  bool IsVarArg,
1043  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
1044  const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
1045  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1046  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1047  M68kMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo<M68kMachineFunctionInfo>();
1048 
1049  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
1050  CCState CCInfo(CCID, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, *DAG.getContext());
1051  CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_M68k);
1052 
1053  SDValue Flag;
1054  SmallVector<SDValue, 6> RetOps;
1055  // Operand #0 = Chain (updated below)
1056  RetOps.push_back(Chain);
1057  // Operand #1 = Bytes To Pop
1058  RetOps.push_back(
1059  DAG.getTargetConstant(MFI->getBytesToPopOnReturn(), DL, MVT::i32));
1060 
1061  // Copy the result values into the output registers.
1062  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RVLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1063  CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
1064  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
1065  SDValue ValToCopy = OutVals[i];
1066  EVT ValVT = ValToCopy.getValueType();
1067 
1068  // Promote values to the appropriate types.
1069  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::SExt)
1070  ValToCopy = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), ValToCopy);
1071  else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExt)
1072  ValToCopy = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), ValToCopy);
1073  else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::AExt) {
1074  if (ValVT.isVector() && ValVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
1075  ValToCopy = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), ValToCopy);
1076  else
1077  ValToCopy = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), ValToCopy);
1078  } else if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::BCvt)
1079  ValToCopy = DAG.getBitcast(VA.getLocVT(), ValToCopy);
1080 
1081  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), ValToCopy, Flag);
1082  Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
1083  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
1084  }
1085 
1086  // Swift calling convention does not require we copy the sret argument
1087  // into %d0 for the return, and SRetReturnReg is not set for Swift.
1088 
1089  // ABI require that for returning structs by value we copy the sret argument
1090  // into %D0 for the return. Save the argument into a virtual register so that
1091  // we can access it from the return points.
1092  //
1093  // Checking Function.hasStructRetAttr() here is insufficient because the IR
1094  // may not have an explicit sret argument. If MFI.CanLowerReturn is
1095  // false, then an sret argument may be implicitly inserted in the SelDAG. In
1096  // either case MFI->setSRetReturnReg() will have been called.
1097  if (unsigned SRetReg = MFI->getSRetReturnReg()) {
1098  // ??? Can i just move this to the top and escape this explanation?
1099  // When we have both sret and another return value, we should use the
1100  // original Chain stored in RetOps[0], instead of the current Chain updated
1101  // in the above loop. If we only have sret, RetOps[0] equals to Chain.
1102 
1103  // For the case of sret and another return value, we have
1104  // Chain_0 at the function entry
1105  // Chain_1 = getCopyToReg(Chain_0) in the above loop
1106  // If we use Chain_1 in getCopyFromReg, we will have
1107  // Val = getCopyFromReg(Chain_1)
1108  // Chain_2 = getCopyToReg(Chain_1, Val) from below
1109 
1110  // getCopyToReg(Chain_0) will be glued together with
1111  // getCopyToReg(Chain_1, Val) into Unit A, getCopyFromReg(Chain_1) will be
1112  // in Unit B, and we will have cyclic dependency between Unit A and Unit B:
1113  // Data dependency from Unit B to Unit A due to usage of Val in
1114  // getCopyToReg(Chain_1, Val)
1115  // Chain dependency from Unit A to Unit B
1116 
1117  // So here, we use RetOps[0] (i.e Chain_0) for getCopyFromReg.
1118  SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(RetOps[0], DL, SRetReg,
1119  getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout()));
1120 
1121  // ??? How will this work if CC does not use registers for args passing?
1122  // ??? What if I return multiple structs?
1123  unsigned RetValReg = M68k::D0;
1124  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RetValReg, Val, Flag);
1125  Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
1126 
1127  RetOps.push_back(
1128  DAG.getRegister(RetValReg, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
1129  }
1130 
1131  RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
1132 
1133  // Add the flag if we have it.
1134  if (Flag.getNode())
1135  RetOps.push_back(Flag);
1136 
1137  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::RET, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
1138 }

1140 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1141 // Fast Calling Convention (tail call) implementation
1142 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1143 
1144 // Like std call, callee cleans arguments, convention except that ECX is
1145 // reserved for storing the tail called function address. Only 2 registers are
1146 // free for argument passing (inreg). Tail call optimization is performed
1147 // provided:
1148 // * tailcallopt is enabled
1149 // * caller/callee are fastcc
1150 // On M68k_64 architecture with GOT-style position independent code only
1151 // local (within module) calls are supported at the moment. To keep the stack
1152 // aligned according to platform abi the function GetAlignedArgumentStackSize
1153 // ensures that argument delta is always multiples of stack alignment. (Dynamic
1154 // linkers need this - darwin's dyld for example) If a tail called function
1155 // callee has more arguments than the caller the caller needs to make sure that
1156 // there is room to move the RETADDR to. This is achieved by reserving an area
1157 // the size of the argument delta right after the original RETADDR, but before
1158 // the saved framepointer or the spilled registers e.g. caller(arg1, arg2)
1159 // calls callee(arg1, arg2,arg3,arg4) stack layout:
1160 // arg1
1161 // arg2
1162 // RETADDR
1163 // [ new RETADDR
1164 // move area ]
1165 // (possible EBP)
1166 // ESI
1167 // EDI
1168 // local1 ..
1169 
1170 /// Make the stack size align e.g 16n + 12 aligned for a 16-byte align
1171 /// requirement.
1172 unsigned
1173 M68kTargetLowering::GetAlignedArgumentStackSize(unsigned StackSize,
1174  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1175  const TargetFrameLowering &TFI = *Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
1176  unsigned StackAlignment = TFI.getStackAlignment();
1177  uint64_t AlignMask = StackAlignment - 1;
1178  int64_t Offset = StackSize;
1179  unsigned SlotSize = Subtarget.getSlotSize();
1180  if ((Offset & AlignMask) <= (StackAlignment - SlotSize)) {
1181  // Number smaller than 12 so just add the difference.
1182  Offset += ((StackAlignment - SlotSize) - (Offset & AlignMask));
1183  } else {
1184  // Mask out lower bits, add stackalignment once plus the 12 bytes.
1185  Offset =
1186  ((~AlignMask) & Offset) + StackAlignment + (StackAlignment - SlotSize);
1187  }
1188  return Offset;
1189 }
1190 
1191 /// Check whether the call is eligible for tail call optimization. Targets
1192 /// that want to do tail call optimization should implement this function.
1193 bool M68kTargetLowering::IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
1194  SDValue Callee, CallingConv::ID CalleeCC, bool IsVarArg,
1195  bool IsCalleeStructRet, bool IsCallerStructRet, Type *RetTy,
1196  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
1197  const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
1198  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1199  if (!mayTailCallThisCC(CalleeCC))
1200  return false;
1201 
1202  // If -tailcallopt is specified, make fastcc functions tail-callable.
1203  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1204  const auto &CallerF = MF.getFunction();
1205 
1206  CallingConv::ID CallerCC = CallerF.getCallingConv();
1207  bool CCMatch = CallerCC == CalleeCC;
1208 
1209  if (DAG.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt) {
1210  if (canGuaranteeTCO(CalleeCC) && CCMatch)
1211  return true;
1212  return false;
1213  }
1214 
1215  // Look for obvious safe cases to perform tail call optimization that do not
1216  // require ABI changes. This is what gcc calls sibcall.
1217 
1218  // Can't do sibcall if stack needs to be dynamically re-aligned. PEI needs to
1219  // emit a special epilogue.
1220  const M68kRegisterInfo *RegInfo = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
1221  if (RegInfo->hasStackRealignment(MF))
1222  return false;
1223 
1224  // Also avoid sibcall optimization if either caller or callee uses struct
1225  // return semantics.
1226  if (IsCalleeStructRet || IsCallerStructRet)
1227  return false;
1228 
1229  // Do not sibcall optimize vararg calls unless all arguments are passed via
1230  // registers.
1231  LLVMContext &C = *DAG.getContext();
1232  if (IsVarArg && !Outs.empty()) {
1233 
1234  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
1235  CCState CCInfo(CalleeCC, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, C);
1236 
1237  CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_M68k);
1238  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i)
1239  if (!ArgLocs[i].isRegLoc())
1240  return false;
1241  }
1242 
1243  // Check that the call results are passed in the same way.
1244  if (!CCState::resultsCompatible(CalleeCC, CallerCC, MF, C, Ins, RetCC_M68k,
1245  RetCC_M68k))
1246  return false;
1247 
1248  // The callee has to preserve all registers the caller needs to preserve.
1249  const M68kRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
1250  const uint32_t *CallerPreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallerCC);
1251  if (!CCMatch) {
1252  const uint32_t *CalleePreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CalleeCC);
1253  if (!TRI->regmaskSubsetEqual(CallerPreserved, CalleePreserved))
1254  return false;
1255  }
1256 
1257  unsigned StackArgsSize = 0;
1258 
1259  // If the callee takes no arguments then go on to check the results of the
1260  // call.
1261  if (!Outs.empty()) {
1262  // Check if stack adjustment is needed. For now, do not do this if any
1263  // argument is passed on the stack.
1264  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
1265  CCState CCInfo(CalleeCC, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, C);
1266 
1267  CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_M68k);
1268  StackArgsSize = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
1269 
1270  if (CCInfo.getNextStackOffset()) {
1271  // Check if the arguments are already laid out in the right way as
1272  // the caller's fixed stack objects.
1273  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
1274  const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI = &MF.getRegInfo();
1275  const M68kInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
1276  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1277  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
1278  SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
1279  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
1280  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
1281  return false;
1282  if (!VA.isRegLoc()) {
1283  if (!MatchingStackOffset(Arg, VA.getLocMemOffset(), Flags, MFI, MRI,
1284  TII, VA))
1285  return false;
1286  }
1287  }
1288  }
1289 
1290  bool PositionIndependent = isPositionIndependent();
1291  // If the tailcall address may be in a register, then make sure it's
1292  // possible to register allocate for it. The call address can
1293  // only target %A0 or %A1 since the tail call must be scheduled after
1294  // callee-saved registers are restored. These happen to be the same
1295  // registers used to pass 'inreg' arguments so watch out for those.
1296  if ((!isa<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee) &&
1297  !isa<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) ||
1298  PositionIndependent) {
1299  unsigned NumInRegs = 0;
1300  // In PIC we need an extra register to formulate the address computation
1301  // for the callee.
1302  unsigned MaxInRegs = PositionIndependent ? 1 : 2;
1303 
1304  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1305  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
1306  if (!VA.isRegLoc())
1307  continue;
1308  Register Reg = VA.getLocReg();
1309  switch (Reg) {
1310  default:
1311  break;
1312  case M68k::A0:
1313  case M68k::A1:
1314  if (++NumInRegs == MaxInRegs)
1315  return false;
1316  break;
1317  }
1318  }
1319  }
1320 
1321  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
1322  if (!parametersInCSRMatch(MRI, CallerPreserved, ArgLocs, OutVals))
1323  return false;
1324  }
1325 
1326  bool CalleeWillPop = M68k::isCalleePop(
1327  CalleeCC, IsVarArg, MF.getTarget().Options.GuaranteedTailCallOpt);
1328 
1329  if (unsigned BytesToPop =
1330  MF.getInfo<M68kMachineFunctionInfo>()->getBytesToPopOnReturn()) {
1331  // If we have bytes to pop, the callee must pop them.
1332  bool CalleePopMatches = CalleeWillPop && BytesToPop == StackArgsSize;
1333  if (!CalleePopMatches)
1334  return false;
1335  } else if (CalleeWillPop && StackArgsSize > 0) {
1336  // If we don't have bytes to pop, make sure the callee doesn't pop any.
1337  return false;
1338  }
1339 
1340  return true;
1341 }

1395 bool M68kTargetLowering::decomposeMulByConstant(LLVMContext &Context, EVT VT,
1396  SDValue C) const {
1397  // Shifts and add instructions in M68000 and M68010 support
1398  // up to 32 bits, but mul only has 16-bit variant. So it's almost
1399  // certainly beneficial to lower 8/16/32-bit mul to their
1400  // add / shifts counterparts. But for 64-bits mul, it might be
1401  // safer to just leave it to compiler runtime implementations.
1402  return VT.bitsLE(MVT::i32) || Subtarget.atLeastM68020();
1403 }

1405 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerXALUO(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1406  // Lower the "add/sub/mul with overflow" instruction into a regular ins plus
1407  // a "setcc" instruction that checks the overflow flag. The "brcond" lowering
1408  // looks for this combo and may remove the "setcc" instruction if the "setcc"
1409  // has only one use.
1410  SDNode *N = Op.getNode();
1411  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
1412  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
1413  unsigned BaseOp = 0;
1414  unsigned Cond = 0;
1415  SDLoc DL(Op);
1416  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
1417  default:
1418  llvm_unreachable("Unknown ovf instruction!");
1419  case ISD::SADDO:
1420  BaseOp = M68kISD::ADD;
1421  Cond = M68k::COND_VS;
1422  break;
1423  case ISD::UADDO:
1424  BaseOp = M68kISD::ADD;
1425  Cond = M68k::COND_CS;
1426  break;
1427  case ISD::SSUBO:
1428  BaseOp = M68kISD::SUB;
1429  Cond = M68k::COND_VS;
1430  break;
1431  case ISD::USUBO:
1432  BaseOp = M68kISD::SUB;
1433  Cond = M68k::COND_CS;
1434  break;
1435  }
1436 
1437  // Also sets CCR.
1438  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(N->getValueType(0), MVT::i8);
1439  SDValue Arith = DAG.getNode(BaseOp, DL, VTs, LHS, RHS);
1440  SDValue SetCC = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, DL, N->getValueType(1),
1441  DAG.getConstant(Cond, DL, MVT::i8),
1442  SDValue(Arith.getNode(), 1));
1443 
1444  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MERGE_VALUES, DL, N->getVTList(), Arith, SetCC);
1445 }

1447 /// Create a BTST (Bit Test) node - Test bit \p BitNo in \p Src and set
1448 /// condition according to equal/not-equal condition code \p CC.
1449 static SDValue getBitTestCondition(SDValue Src, SDValue BitNo, ISD::CondCode CC,
1450  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1451  // If Src is i8, promote it to i32 with any_extend. There is no i8 BTST
1452  // instruction. Since the shift amount is in-range-or-undefined, we know
1453  // that doing a bittest on the i32 value is ok.
1454  if (Src.getValueType() == MVT::i8 || Src.getValueType() == MVT::i16)
1455  Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, Src);
1456 
1457  // If the operand types disagree, extend the shift amount to match. Since
1458  // BTST ignores high bits (like shifts) we can use anyextend.
1459  if (Src.getValueType() != BitNo.getValueType())
1460  BitNo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, Src.getValueType(), BitNo);
1461 
1462  SDValue BTST = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::BTST, DL, MVT::i32, Src, BitNo);
1463 
1464  // NOTE BTST sets CCR.Z flag
1465  M68k::CondCode Cond = CC == ISD::SETEQ ? M68k::COND_NE : M68k::COND_EQ;
1466  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i8,
1467  DAG.getConstant(Cond, DL, MVT::i8), BTST);
1468 }

1470 /// Result of 'and' is compared against zero. Change to a BTST node if possible.
1471 static SDValue LowerAndToBTST(SDValue And, ISD::CondCode CC, const SDLoc &DL,
1472  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1473  SDValue Op0 = And.getOperand(0);
1474  SDValue Op1 = And.getOperand(1);
1475  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
1476  Op0 = Op0.getOperand(0);
1477  if (Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
1478  Op1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
1479 
1480  SDValue LHS, RHS;
1481  if (Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL)
1482  std::swap(Op0, Op1);
1483  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
1484  if (isOneConstant(Op0.getOperand(0))) {
1485  // If we looked past a truncate, check that it's only truncating away
1486  // known zeros.
1487  unsigned BitWidth = Op0.getValueSizeInBits();
1488  unsigned AndBitWidth = And.getValueSizeInBits();
1489  if (BitWidth > AndBitWidth) {
1490  auto Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op0);
1491  if (Known.countMinLeadingZeros() < BitWidth - AndBitWidth)
1492  return SDValue();
1493  }
1494  LHS = Op1;
1495  RHS = Op0.getOperand(1);
1496  }
1497  } else if (auto *AndRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op1)) {
1498  uint64_t AndRHSVal = AndRHS->getZExtValue();
1499  SDValue AndLHS = Op0;
1500 
1501  if (AndRHSVal == 1 && AndLHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
1502  LHS = AndLHS.getOperand(0);
1503  RHS = AndLHS.getOperand(1);
1504  }
1505 
1506  // Use BTST if the immediate can't be encoded in a TEST instruction.
1507  if (!isUInt<32>(AndRHSVal) && isPowerOf2_64(AndRHSVal)) {
1508  LHS = AndLHS;
1509  RHS = DAG.getConstant(Log2_64_Ceil(AndRHSVal), DL, LHS.getValueType());
1510  }
1511  }
1512 
1513  if (LHS.getNode())
1514  return getBitTestCondition(LHS, RHS, CC, DL, DAG);
1515 
1516  return SDValue();
1517 }

1519 static M68k::CondCode TranslateIntegerM68kCC(ISD::CondCode SetCCOpcode) {
1520  switch (SetCCOpcode) {
1521  default:
1522  llvm_unreachable("Invalid integer condition!");
1523  case ISD::SETEQ:
1524  return M68k::COND_EQ;
1525  case ISD::SETGT:
1526  return M68k::COND_GT;
1527  case ISD::SETGE:
1528  return M68k::COND_GE;
1529  case ISD::SETLT:
1530  return M68k::COND_LT;
1531  case ISD::SETLE:
1532  return M68k::COND_LE;
1533  case ISD::SETNE:
1534  return M68k::COND_NE;
1535  case ISD::SETULT:
1536  return M68k::COND_CS;
1537  case ISD::SETUGE:
1538  return M68k::COND_CC;
1539  case ISD::SETUGT:
1540  return M68k::COND_HI;
1541  case ISD::SETULE:
1542  return M68k::COND_LS;
1543  }
1544 }

1546 /// Do a one-to-one translation of a ISD::CondCode to the M68k-specific
1547 /// condition code, returning the condition code and the LHS/RHS of the
1548 /// comparison to make.
1549 static unsigned TranslateM68kCC(ISD::CondCode SetCCOpcode, const SDLoc &DL,
1550  bool IsFP, SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS,
1551  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1552  if (!IsFP) {
1553  if (ConstantSDNode *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
1554  if (SetCCOpcode == ISD::SETGT && RHSC->isAllOnesValue()) {
1555  // X > -1 -> X == 0, jump !sign.
1556  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, RHS.getValueType());
1557  return M68k::COND_PL;
1558  }
1559  if (SetCCOpcode == ISD::SETLT && RHSC->isNullValue()) {
1560  // X < 0 -> X == 0, jump on sign.
1561  return M68k::COND_MI;
1562  }
1563  if (SetCCOpcode == ISD::SETLT && RHSC->getZExtValue() == 1) {
1564  // X < 1 -> X <= 0
1565  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, RHS.getValueType());
1566  return M68k::COND_LE;
1567  }
1568  }
1569 
1570  return TranslateIntegerM68kCC(SetCCOpcode);
1571  }
1572 
1573  // First determine if it is required or is profitable to flip the operands.
1574 
1575  // If LHS is a foldable load, but RHS is not, flip the condition.
1576  if (ISD::isNON_EXTLoad(LHS.getNode()) && !ISD::isNON_EXTLoad(RHS.getNode())) {
1577  SetCCOpcode = getSetCCSwappedOperands(SetCCOpcode);
1578  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
1579  }
1580 
1581  switch (SetCCOpcode) {
1582  default:
1583  break;
1584  case ISD::SETOLT:
1585  case ISD::SETOLE:
1586  case ISD::SETUGT:
1587  case ISD::SETUGE:
1588  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
1589  break;
1590  }
1591 
1592  // On a floating point condition, the flags are set as follows:
1593  // ZF PF CF op
1594  // 0 | 0 | 0 | X > Y
1595  // 0 | 0 | 1 | X < Y
1596  // 1 | 0 | 0 | X == Y
1597  // 1 | 1 | 1 | unordered
1598  switch (SetCCOpcode) {
1599  default:
1600  llvm_unreachable("Condcode should be pre-legalized away");
1601  case ISD::SETUEQ:
1602  case ISD::SETEQ:
1603  return M68k::COND_EQ;
1604  case ISD::SETOLT: // flipped
1605  case ISD::SETOGT:
1606  case ISD::SETGT:
1607  return M68k::COND_HI;
1608  case ISD::SETOLE: // flipped
1609  case ISD::SETOGE:
1610  case ISD::SETGE:
1611  return M68k::COND_CC;
1612  case ISD::SETUGT: // flipped
1613  case ISD::SETULT:
1614  case ISD::SETLT:
1615  return M68k::COND_CS;
1616  case ISD::SETUGE: // flipped
1617  case ISD::SETULE:
1618  case ISD::SETLE:
1619  return M68k::COND_LS;
1620  case ISD::SETONE:
1621  case ISD::SETNE:
1622  return M68k::COND_NE;
1623  case ISD::SETOEQ:
1624  case ISD::SETUNE:
1625  return M68k::COND_INVALID;
1626  }
1627 }

1629 // Convert (truncate (srl X, N) to i1) to (bt X, N)
1630 static SDValue LowerTruncateToBTST(SDValue Op, ISD::CondCode CC,
1631  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1632 
1633  assert(Op.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE && Op.getValueType() == MVT::i1 &&
1634  "Expected TRUNCATE to i1 node");
1635 
1636  if (Op.getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::SRL)
1637  return SDValue();
1638 
1639  SDValue ShiftRight = Op.getOperand(0);
1640  return getBitTestCondition(ShiftRight.getOperand(0), ShiftRight.getOperand(1),
1641  CC, DL, DAG);

1644 /// \brief return true if \c Op has a use that doesn't just read flags.
1645 static bool hasNonFlagsUse(SDValue Op) {
1646  for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = Op->use_begin(), UE = Op->use_end(); UI != UE;
1647  ++UI) {
1648  SDNode *User = *UI;
1649  unsigned UOpNo = UI.getOperandNo();
1650  if (User->getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE && User->hasOneUse()) {
1651  // Look pass truncate.
1652  UOpNo = User->use_begin().getOperandNo();
1653  User = *User->use_begin();
1654  }
1655 
1656  if (User->getOpcode() != ISD::BRCOND && User->getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC &&
1657  !(User->getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT && UOpNo == 0))
1658  return true;
1659  }
1660  return false;
1661 }
1662 
1663 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::EmitTest(SDValue Op, unsigned M68kCC,
1664  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1665 
1666  // CF and OF aren't always set the way we want. Determine which
1667  // of these we need.
1668  bool NeedCF = false;
1669  bool NeedOF = false;
1670  switch (M68kCC) {
1671  default:
1672  break;
1673  case M68k::COND_HI:
1674  case M68k::COND_CC:
1675  case M68k::COND_CS:
1676  case M68k::COND_LS:
1677  NeedCF = true;
1678  break;
1679  case M68k::COND_GT:
1680  case M68k::COND_GE:
1681  case M68k::COND_LT:
1682  case M68k::COND_LE:
1683  case M68k::COND_VS:
1684  case M68k::COND_VC: {
1685  // Check if we really need to set the
1686  // Overflow flag. If NoSignedWrap is present
1687  // that is not actually needed.
1688  switch (Op->getOpcode()) {
1689  case ISD::ADD:
1690  case ISD::SUB:
1691  case ISD::MUL:
1692  case ISD::SHL: {
1693  if (Op.getNode()->getFlags().hasNoSignedWrap())
1694  break;
1695  [[fallthrough]];
1696  }
1697  default:
1698  NeedOF = true;
1699  break;
1700  }
1701  break;
1702  }
1703  }
1704  // See if we can use the CCR value from the operand instead of
1705  // doing a separate TEST. TEST always sets OF and CF to 0, so unless
1706  // we prove that the arithmetic won't overflow, we can't use OF or CF.
1707  if (Op.getResNo() != 0 || NeedOF || NeedCF) {
1708  // Emit a CMP with 0, which is the TEST pattern.
1709  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMP, DL, MVT::i8,
1710  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Op.getValueType()), Op);
1711  }
1712  unsigned Opcode = 0;
1713  unsigned NumOperands = 0;
1714 
1715  // Truncate operations may prevent the merge of the SETCC instruction
1716  // and the arithmetic instruction before it. Attempt to truncate the operands
1717  // of the arithmetic instruction and use a reduced bit-width instruction.
1718  bool NeedTruncation = false;
1719  SDValue ArithOp = Op;
1720  if (Op->getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE && Op->hasOneUse()) {
1721  SDValue Arith = Op->getOperand(0);
1722  // Both the trunc and the arithmetic op need to have one user each.
1723  if (Arith->hasOneUse())
1724  switch (Arith.getOpcode()) {
1725  default:
1726  break;
1727  case ISD::ADD:
1728  case ISD::SUB:
1729  case ISD::AND:
1730  case ISD::OR:
1731  case ISD::XOR: {
1732  NeedTruncation = true;
1733  ArithOp = Arith;
1734  }
1735  }
1736  }
1737 
1738  // NOTICE: In the code below we use ArithOp to hold the arithmetic operation
1739  // which may be the result of a CAST. We use the variable 'Op', which is the
1740  // non-casted variable when we check for possible users.
1741  switch (ArithOp.getOpcode()) {
1742  case ISD::ADD:
1743  Opcode = M68kISD::ADD;
1744  NumOperands = 2;
1745  break;
1746  case ISD::SHL:
1747  case ISD::SRL:
1748  // If we have a constant logical shift that's only used in a comparison
1749  // against zero turn it into an equivalent AND. This allows turning it into
1750  // a TEST instruction later.
1751  if ((M68kCC == M68k::COND_EQ || M68kCC == M68k::COND_NE) &&
1752  Op->hasOneUse() && isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op->getOperand(1)) &&
1753  !hasNonFlagsUse(Op)) {
1754  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
1755  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
1756  unsigned ShAmt = Op->getConstantOperandVal(1);
1757  if (ShAmt >= BitWidth) // Avoid undefined shifts.
1758  break;
1759  APInt Mask = ArithOp.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL
1760  ? APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - ShAmt)
1761  : APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - ShAmt);
1762  if (!Mask.isSignedIntN(32)) // Avoid large immediates.
1763  break;
1764  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Op->getOperand(0),
1765  DAG.getConstant(Mask, DL, VT));
1766  }
1767  break;
1768 
1769  case ISD::AND:
1770  // If the primary 'and' result isn't used, don't bother using
1771  // M68kISD::AND, because a TEST instruction will be better.
1772  if (!hasNonFlagsUse(Op)) {
1773  SDValue Op0 = ArithOp->getOperand(0);
1774  SDValue Op1 = ArithOp->getOperand(1);
1775  EVT VT = ArithOp.getValueType();
1776  bool IsAndn = isBitwiseNot(Op0) || isBitwiseNot(Op1);
1777  bool IsLegalAndnType = VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64;
1778 
1779  // But if we can combine this into an ANDN operation, then create an AND
1780  // now and allow it to be pattern matched into an ANDN.
1781  if (/*!Subtarget.hasBMI() ||*/ !IsAndn || !IsLegalAndnType)
1782  break;
1783  }
1784  [[fallthrough]];
1785  case ISD::SUB:
1786  case ISD::OR:
1787  case ISD::XOR:
1788  // Due to the ISEL shortcoming noted above, be conservative if this op is
1789  // likely to be selected as part of a load-modify-store instruction.
1790  for (const auto *U : Op.getNode()->uses())
1791  if (U->getOpcode() == ISD::STORE)
1792  goto default_case;
1793 
1794  // Otherwise use a regular CCR-setting instruction.
1795  switch (ArithOp.getOpcode()) {
1796  default:
1797  llvm_unreachable("unexpected operator!");
1798  case ISD::SUB:
1799  Opcode = M68kISD::SUB;
1800  break;
1801  case ISD::XOR:
1802  Opcode = M68kISD::XOR;
1803  break;
1804  case ISD::AND:
1805  Opcode = M68kISD::AND;
1806  break;
1807  case ISD::OR:
1808  Opcode = M68kISD::OR;
1809  break;
1810  }
1811 
1812  NumOperands = 2;
1813  break;
1814  case M68kISD::ADD:
1815  case M68kISD::SUB:
1816  case M68kISD::OR:
1817  case M68kISD::XOR:
1818  case M68kISD::AND:
1819  return SDValue(Op.getNode(), 1);
1820  default:
1821  default_case:
1822  break;
1823  }
1824 
1825  // If we found that truncation is beneficial, perform the truncation and
1826  // update 'Op'.
1827  if (NeedTruncation) {
1828  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
1829  SDValue WideVal = Op->getOperand(0);
1830  EVT WideVT = WideVal.getValueType();
1831  unsigned ConvertedOp = 0;
1832  // Use a target machine opcode to prevent further DAGCombine
1833  // optimizations that may separate the arithmetic operations
1834  // from the setcc node.
1835  switch (WideVal.getOpcode()) {
1836  default:
1837  break;
1838  case ISD::ADD:
1839  ConvertedOp = M68kISD::ADD;
1840  break;
1841  case ISD::SUB:
1842  ConvertedOp = M68kISD::SUB;
1843  break;
1844  case ISD::AND:
1845  ConvertedOp = M68kISD::AND;
1846  break;
1847  case ISD::OR:
1848  ConvertedOp = M68kISD::OR;
1849  break;
1850  case ISD::XOR:
1851  ConvertedOp = M68kISD::XOR;
1852  break;
1853  }
1854 
1855  if (ConvertedOp) {
1856  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
1857  if (TLI.isOperationLegal(WideVal.getOpcode(), WideVT)) {
1858  SDValue V0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, WideVal.getOperand(0));
1859  SDValue V1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, WideVal.getOperand(1));
1860  Op = DAG.getNode(ConvertedOp, DL, VT, V0, V1);
1861  }
1862  }
1863  }
1864 
1865  if (Opcode == 0) {
1866  // Emit a CMP with 0, which is the TEST pattern.
1867  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMP, DL, MVT::i8,
1868  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Op.getValueType()), Op);
1869  }
1870  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Op.getValueType(), MVT::i8);
1871  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops(Op->op_begin(), Op->op_begin() + NumOperands);
1872 
1873  SDValue New = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, Ops);
1874  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Op, New);
1875  return SDValue(New.getNode(), 1);
1876 }
1877 
1878 /// \brief Return true if the condition is an unsigned comparison operation.
1879 static bool isM68kCCUnsigned(unsigned M68kCC) {
1880  switch (M68kCC) {
1881  default:
1882  llvm_unreachable("Invalid integer condition!");
1883  case M68k::COND_EQ:
1884  case M68k::COND_NE:
1885  case M68k::COND_CS:
1886  case M68k::COND_HI:
1887  case M68k::COND_LS:
1888  case M68k::COND_CC:
1889  return true;
1890  case M68k::COND_GT:
1891  case M68k::COND_GE:
1892  case M68k::COND_LT:
1893  case M68k::COND_LE:
1894  return false;
1895  }
1896 }

1898 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::EmitCmp(SDValue Op0, SDValue Op1, unsigned M68kCC,
1899  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1900  if (isNullConstant(Op1))
1901  return EmitTest(Op0, M68kCC, DL, DAG);
1902 
1903  assert(!(isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op1) && Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i1) &&
1904  "Unexpected comparison operation for MVT::i1 operands");
1905 
1906  if ((Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i8 || Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i16 ||
1907  Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i32 || Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i64)) {
1908  // Only promote the compare up to I32 if it is a 16 bit operation
1909  // with an immediate. 16 bit immediates are to be avoided.
1910  if ((Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i16 &&
1911  (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op0) || isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op1))) &&
1912  !DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().hasMinSize()) {
1913  unsigned ExtendOp =
1914  isM68kCCUnsigned(M68kCC) ? ISD::ZERO_EXTEND : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
1915  Op0 = DAG.getNode(ExtendOp, DL, MVT::i32, Op0);
1916  Op1 = DAG.getNode(ExtendOp, DL, MVT::i32, Op1);
1917  }
1918  // Use SUB instead of CMP to enable CSE between SUB and CMP.
1919  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Op0.getValueType(), MVT::i8);
1920  SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SUB, DL, VTs, Op0, Op1);
1921  return SDValue(Sub.getNode(), 1);
1922  }
1923  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMP, DL, MVT::i8, Op0, Op1);
1924 }

1926 /// Result of 'and' or 'trunc to i1' is compared against zero.
1927 /// Change to a BTST node if possible.
1928 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerToBTST(SDValue Op, ISD::CondCode CC,
1929  const SDLoc &DL,
1930  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1931  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::AND)
1932  return LowerAndToBTST(Op, CC, DL, DAG);
1933  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE && Op.getValueType() == MVT::i1)
1934  return LowerTruncateToBTST(Op, CC, DL, DAG);
1935  return SDValue();
1936 }

1938 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerSETCC(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1939  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
1940  assert(VT == MVT::i8 && "SetCC type must be 8-bit integer");
1941 
1942  SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1943  SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1944  SDLoc DL(Op);
1945  ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
1946 
1947  // Optimize to BTST if possible.
1948  // Lower (X & (1 << N)) == 0 to BTST(X, N).
1949  // Lower ((X >>u N) & 1) != 0 to BTST(X, N).
1950  // Lower ((X >>s N) & 1) != 0 to BTST(X, N).
1951  // Lower (trunc (X >> N) to i1) to BTST(X, N).
1952  if (Op0.hasOneUse() && isNullConstant(Op1) &&
1953  (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE)) {
1954  if (SDValue NewSetCC = LowerToBTST(Op0, CC, DL, DAG)) {
1955  if (VT == MVT::i1)
1956  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i1, NewSetCC);
1957  return NewSetCC;
1958  }
1959  }
1960 
1961  // Look for X == 0, X == 1, X != 0, or X != 1. We can simplify some forms of
1962  // these.
1963  if ((isOneConstant(Op1) || isNullConstant(Op1)) &&
1964  (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE)) {
1965 
1966  // If the input is a setcc, then reuse the input setcc or use a new one with
1967  // the inverted condition.
1968  if (Op0.getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC) {
1969  M68k::CondCode CCode = (M68k::CondCode)Op0.getConstantOperandVal(0);
1970  bool Invert = (CC == ISD::SETNE) ^ isNullConstant(Op1);
1971  if (!Invert)
1972  return Op0;
1973 
1974  CCode = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition(CCode);
1975  SDValue SetCC =
1976  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i8,
1977  DAG.getConstant(CCode, DL, MVT::i8), Op0.getOperand(1));
1978  if (VT == MVT::i1)
1979  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i1, SetCC);
1980  return SetCC;
1981  }
1982  }
1983  if (Op0.getValueType() == MVT::i1 && (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE)) {
1984  if (isOneConstant(Op1)) {
1985  ISD::CondCode NewCC = ISD::GlobalISel::getSetCCInverse(CC, true);
1986  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, Op0, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), NewCC);
1987  }
1988  if (!isNullConstant(Op1)) {
1989  SDValue Xor = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i1, Op0, Op1);
1990  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, Xor, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), CC);
1991  }
1992  }
1993 
1994  bool IsFP = Op1.getSimpleValueType().isFloatingPoint();
1995  unsigned M68kCC = TranslateM68kCC(CC, DL, IsFP, Op0, Op1, DAG);
1996  if (M68kCC == M68k::COND_INVALID)
1997  return SDValue();
1998 
1999  SDValue CCR = EmitCmp(Op0, Op1, M68kCC, DL, DAG);
2000  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i8,
2001  DAG.getConstant(M68kCC, DL, MVT::i8), CCR);
2002 }

2004 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerSETCCCARRY(SDValue Op,
2005  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2006  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
2007  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
2008  SDValue Carry = Op.getOperand(2);
2009  SDValue Cond = Op.getOperand(3);
2010  SDLoc DL(Op);
2011 
2012  assert(LHS.getSimpleValueType().isInteger() && "SETCCCARRY is integer only.");
2013  M68k::CondCode CC = TranslateIntegerM68kCC(cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Cond)->get());
2014 
2015  EVT CarryVT = Carry.getValueType();
2016  APInt NegOne = APInt::getAllOnes(CarryVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
2017  Carry = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::ADD, DL, DAG.getVTList(CarryVT, MVT::i32), Carry,
2018  DAG.getConstant(NegOne, DL, CarryVT));
2019 
2020  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), MVT::i32);
2021  SDValue Cmp =
2022  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SUBX, DL, VTs, LHS, RHS, Carry.getValue(1));
2023 
2024  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i8,
2025  DAG.getConstant(CC, DL, MVT::i8), Cmp.getValue(1));
2026 }

2028 /// Return true if opcode is a M68k logical comparison.
2029 static bool isM68kLogicalCmp(SDValue Op) {
2030  unsigned Opc = Op.getNode()->getOpcode();
2031  if (Opc == M68kISD::CMP)
2032  return true;
2033  if (Op.getResNo() == 1 &&
2034  (Opc == M68kISD::ADD || Opc == M68kISD::SUB || Opc == M68kISD::ADDX ||
2035  Opc == M68kISD::SUBX || Opc == M68kISD::SMUL || Opc == M68kISD::UMUL ||
2036  Opc == M68kISD::OR || Opc == M68kISD::XOR || Opc == M68kISD::AND))
2037  return true;
2038 
2039  if (Op.getResNo() == 2 && Opc == M68kISD::UMUL)
2040  return true;
2041 
2042  return false;
2043 }

2056 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2057  bool addTest = true;
2058  SDValue Cond = Op.getOperand(0);
2059  SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
2060  SDValue Op2 = Op.getOperand(2);
2061  SDLoc DL(Op);
2062  SDValue CC;
2063 
2064  if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
2065  if (SDValue NewCond = LowerSETCC(Cond, DAG))
2066  Cond = NewCond;
2067  }
2068 
2069  // (select (x == 0), -1, y) -> (sign_bit (x - 1)) | y
2070  // (select (x == 0), y, -1) -> ~(sign_bit (x - 1)) | y
2071  // (select (x != 0), y, -1) -> (sign_bit (x - 1)) | y
2072  // (select (x != 0), -1, y) -> ~(sign_bit (x - 1)) | y
2073  if (Cond.getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC &&
2074  Cond.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == M68kISD::CMP &&
2075  isNullConstant(Cond.getOperand(1).getOperand(0))) {
2076  SDValue Cmp = Cond.getOperand(1);
2077 
2078  unsigned CondCode =
2079  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Cond.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
2080 
2081  if ((isAllOnesConstant(Op1) || isAllOnesConstant(Op2)) &&
2082  (CondCode == M68k::COND_EQ || CondCode == M68k::COND_NE)) {
2083  SDValue Y = isAllOnesConstant(Op2) ? Op1 : Op2;
2084 
2085  SDValue CmpOp0 = Cmp.getOperand(1);
2086  // Apply further optimizations for special cases
2087  // (select (x != 0), -1, 0) -> neg & sbb
2088  // (select (x == 0), 0, -1) -> neg & sbb
2089  if (isNullConstant(Y) &&
2090  (isAllOnesConstant(Op1) == (CondCode == M68k::COND_NE))) {
2091 
2092  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(CmpOp0.getValueType(), MVT::i32);
2093 
2094  SDValue Neg =
2095  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SUB, DL, VTs,
2096  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, CmpOp0.getValueType()), CmpOp0);
2097 
2098  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY, DL, Op.getValueType(),
2099  DAG.getConstant(M68k::COND_CS, DL, MVT::i8),
2100  SDValue(Neg.getNode(), 1));
2101  return Res;
2102  }
2103 
2104  Cmp = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMP, DL, MVT::i8,
2105  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, CmpOp0.getValueType()), CmpOp0);
2106 
2107  SDValue Res = // Res = 0 or -1.
2108  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY, DL, Op.getValueType(),
2109  DAG.getConstant(M68k::COND_CS, DL, MVT::i8), Cmp);
2110 
2111  if (isAllOnesConstant(Op1) != (CondCode == M68k::COND_EQ))
2112  Res = DAG.getNOT(DL, Res, Res.getValueType());
2113 
2114  if (!isNullConstant(Op2))
2115  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, Res.getValueType(), Res, Y);
2116  return Res;
2117  }
2118  }
2119 
2120  // Look past (and (setcc_carry (cmp ...)), 1).
2121  if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
2122  Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY &&
2123  isOneConstant(Cond.getOperand(1)))
2124  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0);
2125 
2126  // If condition flag is set by a M68kISD::CMP, then use it as the condition
2127  // setting operand in place of the M68kISD::SETCC.
2128  unsigned CondOpcode = Cond.getOpcode();
2129  if (CondOpcode == M68kISD::SETCC || CondOpcode == M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY) {
2130  CC = Cond.getOperand(0);
2131 
2132  SDValue Cmp = Cond.getOperand(1);
2133  unsigned Opc = Cmp.getOpcode();
2134 
2135  bool IllegalFPCMov = false;
2136 
2137  if ((isM68kLogicalCmp(Cmp) && !IllegalFPCMov) || Opc == M68kISD::BTST) {
2138  Cond = Cmp;
2139  addTest = false;
2140  }
2141  } else if (CondOpcode == ISD::USUBO || CondOpcode == ISD::SSUBO ||
2142  CondOpcode == ISD::UADDO || CondOpcode == ISD::SADDO ||
2143  CondOpcode == ISD::UMULO || CondOpcode == ISD::SMULO) {
2144  SDValue LHS = Cond.getOperand(0);
2145  SDValue RHS = Cond.getOperand(1);
2146  unsigned MxOpcode;
2147  unsigned MxCond;
2148  SDVTList VTs;
2149  switch (CondOpcode) {
2150  case ISD::UADDO:
2151  MxOpcode = M68kISD::ADD;
2152  MxCond = M68k::COND_CS;
2153  break;
2154  case ISD::SADDO:
2155  MxOpcode = M68kISD::ADD;
2156  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2157  break;
2158  case ISD::USUBO:
2159  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SUB;
2160  MxCond = M68k::COND_CS;
2161  break;
2162  case ISD::SSUBO:
2163  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SUB;
2164  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2165  break;
2166  case ISD::UMULO:
2167  MxOpcode = M68kISD::UMUL;
2168  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2169  break;
2170  case ISD::SMULO:
2171  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SMUL;
2172  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2173  break;
2174  default:
2175  llvm_unreachable("unexpected overflowing operator");
2176  }
2177  if (CondOpcode == ISD::UMULO)
2178  VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), LHS.getValueType(), MVT::i32);
2179  else
2180  VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), MVT::i32);
2181 
2182  SDValue MxOp = DAG.getNode(MxOpcode, DL, VTs, LHS, RHS);
2183 
2184  if (CondOpcode == ISD::UMULO)
2185  Cond = MxOp.getValue(2);
2186  else
2187  Cond = MxOp.getValue(1);
2188 
2189  CC = DAG.getConstant(MxCond, DL, MVT::i8);
2190  addTest = false;
2191  }
2192 
2193  if (addTest) {
2194  // Look past the truncate if the high bits are known zero.
2195  if (isTruncWithZeroHighBitsInput(Cond, DAG))
2196  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0);
2197 
2198  // We know the result of AND is compared against zero. Try to match
2199  // it to BT.
2200  if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && Cond.hasOneUse()) {
2201  if (SDValue NewSetCC = LowerToBTST(Cond, ISD::SETNE, DL, DAG)) {
2202  CC = NewSetCC.getOperand(0);
2203  Cond = NewSetCC.getOperand(1);
2204  addTest = false;
2205  }
2206  }
2207  }
2208 
2209  if (addTest) {
2210  CC = DAG.getConstant(M68k::COND_NE, DL, MVT::i8);
2211  Cond = EmitTest(Cond, M68k::COND_NE, DL, DAG);
2212  }
2213 
2214  // a < b ? -1 : 0 -> RES = ~setcc_carry
2215  // a < b ? 0 : -1 -> RES = setcc_carry
2216  // a >= b ? -1 : 0 -> RES = setcc_carry
2217  // a >= b ? 0 : -1 -> RES = ~setcc_carry
2218  if (Cond.getOpcode() == M68kISD::SUB) {
2219  unsigned CondCode = cast<ConstantSDNode>(CC)->getZExtValue();
2220 
2221  if ((CondCode == M68k::COND_CC || CondCode == M68k::COND_CS) &&
2222  (isAllOnesConstant(Op1) || isAllOnesConstant(Op2)) &&
2223  (isNullConstant(Op1) || isNullConstant(Op2))) {
2224  SDValue Res =
2225  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY, DL, Op.getValueType(),
2226  DAG.getConstant(M68k::COND_CS, DL, MVT::i8), Cond);
2227  if (isAllOnesConstant(Op1) != (CondCode == M68k::COND_CS))
2228  return DAG.getNOT(DL, Res, Res.getValueType());
2229  return Res;
2230  }
2231  }
2232 
2233  // M68k doesn't have an i8 cmov. If both operands are the result of a
2234  // truncate widen the cmov and push the truncate through. This avoids
2235  // introducing a new branch during isel and doesn't add any extensions.
2236  if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::i8 && Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE &&
2237  Op2.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
2238  SDValue T1 = Op1.getOperand(0), T2 = Op2.getOperand(0);
2239  if (T1.getValueType() == T2.getValueType() &&
2240  // Block CopyFromReg so partial register stalls are avoided.
2241  T1.getOpcode() != ISD::CopyFromReg &&
2242  T2.getOpcode() != ISD::CopyFromReg) {
2243  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(T1.getValueType(), MVT::Glue);
2244  SDValue Cmov = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMOV, DL, VTs, T2, T1, CC, Cond);
2245  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, Op.getValueType(), Cmov);
2246  }
2247  }
2248 
2249  // M68kISD::CMOV means set the result (which is operand 1) to the RHS if
2250  // condition is true.
2251  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Op.getValueType(), MVT::Glue);
2252  SDValue Ops[] = {Op2, Op1, CC, Cond};
2253  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::CMOV, DL, VTs, Ops);
2254 }
