2256 /// Return true if node is an ISD::AND or ISD::OR of two M68k::SETcc nodes
2257 /// each of which has no other use apart from the AND / OR.
2258 static bool isAndOrOfSetCCs(SDValue Op, unsigned &Opc) {
2259  Opc = Op.getOpcode();
2260  if (Opc != ISD::OR && Opc != ISD::AND)
2261  return false;
2262  return (M68k::IsSETCC(Op.getOperand(0).getOpcode()) &&
2263  Op.getOperand(0).hasOneUse() &&
2264  M68k::IsSETCC(Op.getOperand(1).getOpcode()) &&
2265  Op.getOperand(1).hasOneUse());
2266 }
2267 
2268 /// Return true if node is an ISD::XOR of a M68kISD::SETCC and 1 and that the
2269 /// SETCC node has a single use.
2270 static bool isXor1OfSetCC(SDValue Op) {
2271  if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::XOR)
2272  return false;
2273  if (isOneConstant(Op.getOperand(1)))
2274  return Op.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC &&
2275  Op.getOperand(0).hasOneUse();
2276  return false;
2277 }

2279 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerBRCOND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2280  bool AddTest = true;
2281  SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
2282  SDValue Cond = Op.getOperand(1);
2283  SDValue Dest = Op.getOperand(2);
2284  SDLoc DL(Op);
2285  SDValue CC;
2286  bool Inverted = false;
2287 
2288  if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
2289  // Check for setcc([su]{add,sub}o == 0).
2290  if (cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Cond.getOperand(2))->get() == ISD::SETEQ &&
2291  isNullConstant(Cond.getOperand(1)) &&
2292  Cond.getOperand(0).getResNo() == 1 &&
2293  (Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO ||
2294  Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ||
2295  Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SSUBO ||
2296  Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::USUBO)) {
2297  Inverted = true;
2298  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0);
2299  } else {
2300  if (SDValue NewCond = LowerSETCC(Cond, DAG))
2301  Cond = NewCond;
2302  }
2303  }
2304 
2305  // Look pass (and (setcc_carry (cmp ...)), 1).
2306  if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
2307  Cond.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY &&
2308  isOneConstant(Cond.getOperand(1)))
2309  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0);
2310 
2311  // If condition flag is set by a M68kISD::CMP, then use it as the condition
2312  // setting operand in place of the M68kISD::SETCC.
2313  unsigned CondOpcode = Cond.getOpcode();
2314  if (CondOpcode == M68kISD::SETCC || CondOpcode == M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY) {
2315  CC = Cond.getOperand(0);
2316 
2317  SDValue Cmp = Cond.getOperand(1);
2318  unsigned Opc = Cmp.getOpcode();
2319 
2320  if (isM68kLogicalCmp(Cmp) || Opc == M68kISD::BTST) {
2321  Cond = Cmp;
2322  AddTest = false;
2323  } else {
2324  switch (cast<ConstantSDNode>(CC)->getZExtValue()) {
2325  default:
2326  break;
2327  case M68k::COND_VS:
2328  case M68k::COND_CS:
2329  // These can only come from an arithmetic instruction with overflow,
2330  // e.g. SADDO, UADDO.
2331  Cond = Cond.getNode()->getOperand(1);
2332  AddTest = false;
2333  break;
2334  }
2335  }
2336  }
2337  CondOpcode = Cond.getOpcode();
2338  if (CondOpcode == ISD::UADDO || CondOpcode == ISD::SADDO ||
2339  CondOpcode == ISD::USUBO || CondOpcode == ISD::SSUBO) {
2340  SDValue LHS = Cond.getOperand(0);
2341  SDValue RHS = Cond.getOperand(1);
2342  unsigned MxOpcode;
2343  unsigned MxCond;
2344  SDVTList VTs;
2345  // Keep this in sync with LowerXALUO, otherwise we might create redundant
2346  // instructions that can't be removed afterwards (i.e. M68kISD::ADD and
2347  // M68kISD::INC).
2348  switch (CondOpcode) {
2349  case ISD::UADDO:
2350  MxOpcode = M68kISD::ADD;
2351  MxCond = M68k::COND_CS;
2352  break;
2353  case ISD::SADDO:
2354  MxOpcode = M68kISD::ADD;
2355  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2356  break;
2357  case ISD::USUBO:
2358  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SUB;
2359  MxCond = M68k::COND_CS;
2360  break;
2361  case ISD::SSUBO:
2362  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SUB;
2363  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2364  break;
2365  case ISD::UMULO:
2366  MxOpcode = M68kISD::UMUL;
2367  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2368  break;
2369  case ISD::SMULO:
2370  MxOpcode = M68kISD::SMUL;
2371  MxCond = M68k::COND_VS;
2372  break;
2373  default:
2374  llvm_unreachable("unexpected overflowing operator");
2375  }
2376 
2377  if (Inverted)
2378  MxCond = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition((M68k::CondCode)MxCond);
2379 
2380  if (CondOpcode == ISD::UMULO)
2381  VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), LHS.getValueType(), MVT::i8);
2382  else
2383  VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), MVT::i8);
2384 
2385  SDValue MxOp = DAG.getNode(MxOpcode, DL, VTs, LHS, RHS);
2386 
2387  if (CondOpcode == ISD::UMULO)
2388  Cond = MxOp.getValue(2);
2389  else
2390  Cond = MxOp.getValue(1);
2391 
2392  CC = DAG.getConstant(MxCond, DL, MVT::i8);
2393  AddTest = false;
2394  } else {
2395  unsigned CondOpc;
2396  if (Cond.hasOneUse() && isAndOrOfSetCCs(Cond, CondOpc)) {
2397  SDValue Cmp = Cond.getOperand(0).getOperand(1);
2398  if (CondOpc == ISD::OR) {
2399  // Also, recognize the pattern generated by an FCMP_UNE. We can emit
2400  // two branches instead of an explicit OR instruction with a
2401  // separate test.
2402  if (Cmp == Cond.getOperand(1).getOperand(1) && isM68kLogicalCmp(Cmp)) {
2403  CC = Cond.getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
2404  Chain = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::BRCOND, DL, Op.getValueType(), Chain,
2405  Dest, CC, Cmp);
2406  CC = Cond.getOperand(1).getOperand(0);
2407  Cond = Cmp;
2408  AddTest = false;
2409  }
2410  } else { // ISD::AND
2411  // Also, recognize the pattern generated by an FCMP_OEQ. We can emit
2412  // two branches instead of an explicit AND instruction with a
2413  // separate test. However, we only do this if this block doesn't
2414  // have a fall-through edge, because this requires an explicit
2415  // jmp when the condition is false.
2416  if (Cmp == Cond.getOperand(1).getOperand(1) && isM68kLogicalCmp(Cmp) &&
2417  Op.getNode()->hasOneUse()) {
2418  M68k::CondCode CCode =
2419  (M68k::CondCode)Cond.getOperand(0).getConstantOperandVal(0);
2420  CCode = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition(CCode);
2421  CC = DAG.getConstant(CCode, DL, MVT::i8);
2422  SDNode *User = *Op.getNode()->use_begin();
2423  // Look for an unconditional branch following this conditional branch.
2424  // We need this because we need to reverse the successors in order
2425  // to implement FCMP_OEQ.
2426  if (User->getOpcode() == ISD::BR) {
2427  SDValue FalseBB = User->getOperand(1);
2428  SDNode *NewBR =
2429  DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(User, User->getOperand(0), Dest);
2430  assert(NewBR == User);
2431  (void)NewBR;
2432  Dest = FalseBB;
2433 
2434  Chain = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::BRCOND, DL, Op.getValueType(), Chain,
2435  Dest, CC, Cmp);
2436  M68k::CondCode CCode =
2437  (M68k::CondCode)Cond.getOperand(1).getConstantOperandVal(0);
2438  CCode = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition(CCode);
2439  CC = DAG.getConstant(CCode, DL, MVT::i8);
2440  Cond = Cmp;
2441  AddTest = false;
2442  }
2443  }
2444  }
2445  } else if (Cond.hasOneUse() && isXor1OfSetCC(Cond)) {
2446  // Recognize for xorb (setcc), 1 patterns. The xor inverts the condition.
2447  // It should be transformed during dag combiner except when the condition
2448  // is set by a arithmetics with overflow node.
2449  M68k::CondCode CCode =
2450  (M68k::CondCode)Cond.getOperand(0).getConstantOperandVal(0);
2451  CCode = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition(CCode);
2452  CC = DAG.getConstant(CCode, DL, MVT::i8);
2453  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0).getOperand(1);
2454  AddTest = false;
2455  }
2456  }
2457 
2458  if (AddTest) {
2459  // Look pass the truncate if the high bits are known zero.
2460  if (isTruncWithZeroHighBitsInput(Cond, DAG))
2461  Cond = Cond.getOperand(0);
2462 
2463  // We know the result is compared against zero. Try to match it to BT.
2464  if (Cond.hasOneUse()) {
2465  if (SDValue NewSetCC = LowerToBTST(Cond, ISD::SETNE, DL, DAG)) {
2466  CC = NewSetCC.getOperand(0);
2467  Cond = NewSetCC.getOperand(1);
2468  AddTest = false;
2469  }
2470  }
2471  }
2472 
2473  if (AddTest) {
2474  M68k::CondCode MxCond = Inverted ? M68k::COND_EQ : M68k::COND_NE;
2475  CC = DAG.getConstant(MxCond, DL, MVT::i8);
2476  Cond = EmitTest(Cond, MxCond, DL, DAG);
2477  }
2478  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::BRCOND, DL, Op.getValueType(), Chain, Dest, CC,
2479  Cond);
2480 }

2482 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerADDC_ADDE_SUBC_SUBE(SDValue Op,
2483  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2484  MVT VT = Op.getNode()->getSimpleValueType(0);
2485 
2486  // Let legalize expand this if it isn't a legal type yet.
2487  if (!DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().isTypeLegal(VT))
2488  return SDValue();
2489 
2490  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::i8);
2491 
2492  unsigned Opc;
2493  bool ExtraOp = false;
2494  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
2495  default:
2496  llvm_unreachable("Invalid code");
2497  case ISD::ADDC:
2498  Opc = M68kISD::ADD;
2499  break;
2500  case ISD::ADDE:
2501  Opc = M68kISD::ADDX;
2502  ExtraOp = true;
2503  break;
2504  case ISD::SUBC:
2505  Opc = M68kISD::SUB;
2506  break;
2507  case ISD::SUBE:
2508  Opc = M68kISD::SUBX;

2510  break;

2514  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(Op), VTs, Op.getOperand(0), Op.getOperand(1));
2515  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(Op), VTs, Op.getOperand(0), Op.getOperand(1),
2516  Op.getOperand(2));

2519 // ConstantPool, JumpTable, GlobalAddress, and ExternalSymbol are lowered as
2520 // their target countpart wrapped in the M68kISD::Wrapper node. Suppose N is
2521 // one of the above mentioned nodes. It has to be wrapped because otherwise
2522 // Select(N) returns N. So the raw TargetGlobalAddress nodes, etc. can only
2523 // be used to form addressing mode. These wrapped nodes will be selected
2524 // into MOV32ri.
2525 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerConstantPool(SDValue Op,
2526  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2527  ConstantPoolSDNode *CP = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(Op);
2528 
2529  // In PIC mode (unless we're in PCRel PIC mode) we add an offset to the
2530  // global base reg.
2531  unsigned char OpFlag = Subtarget.classifyLocalReference(nullptr);
2532 
2533  unsigned WrapperKind = M68kISD::Wrapper;
2534  if (M68kII::isPCRelGlobalReference(OpFlag)) {
2535  WrapperKind = M68kISD::WrapperPC;
2536  }
2537 
2538  MVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2539  SDValue Result = DAG.getTargetConstantPool(
2540  CP->getConstVal(), PtrVT, CP->getAlign(), CP->getOffset(), OpFlag);
2541 
2542  SDLoc DL(CP);
2543  Result = DAG.getNode(WrapperKind, DL, PtrVT, Result);
2544 
2545  // With PIC, the address is actually $g + Offset.
2546  if (M68kII::isGlobalRelativeToPICBase(OpFlag)) {
2547  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT,
2548  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::GLOBAL_BASE_REG, SDLoc(), PtrVT),
2549  Result);
2550  }
2551 
2552  return Result;
2553 }

2563

2619 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerGlobalAddress(const GlobalValue *GV,
2620  const SDLoc &DL, int64_t Offset,
2621  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2622  unsigned char OpFlags = Subtarget.classifyGlobalReference(GV);
2623  auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2624 
2625  // Create the TargetGlobalAddress node, folding in the constant
2626  // offset if it is legal.
2627  SDValue Result;
2628  if (M68kII::isDirectGlobalReference(OpFlags)) {
2629  Result = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, Offset);
2630  Offset = 0;
2631  } else {
2632  Result = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, OpFlags);
2633  }
2634 
2635  if (M68kII::isPCRelGlobalReference(OpFlags))
2636  Result = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::WrapperPC, DL, PtrVT, Result);
2637  else
2638  Result = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::Wrapper, DL, PtrVT, Result);
2639 
2640  // With PIC, the address is actually $g + Offset.
2641  if (M68kII::isGlobalRelativeToPICBase(OpFlags)) {
2642  Result =
2643  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT,
2644  DAG.getNode(M68kISD::GLOBAL_BASE_REG, DL, PtrVT), Result);
2645  }
2646 
2647  // For globals that require a load from a stub to get the address, emit the
2648  // load.
2649  if (M68kII::isGlobalStubReference(OpFlags)) {
2650  Result = DAG.getLoad(PtrVT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), Result,
2651  MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()));
2652  }
2653 
2654  // If there was a non-zero offset that we didn't fold, create an explicit
2655  // addition for it.
2656  if (Offset != 0) {
2657  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Result,
2658  DAG.getConstant(Offset, DL, PtrVT));
2659  }
2660 
2661  return Result;
2662 }

2675 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerJumpTable(SDValue Op,
2676  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2677  JumpTableSDNode *JT = cast<JumpTableSDNode>(Op);
2678 
2679  // In PIC mode (unless we're in PCRel PIC mode) we add an offset to the
2680  // global base reg.
2681  unsigned char OpFlag = Subtarget.classifyLocalReference(nullptr);
2682 
2683  unsigned WrapperKind = M68kISD::Wrapper;
2684  if (M68kII::isPCRelGlobalReference(OpFlag)) {
2685  WrapperKind = M68kISD::WrapperPC;
2686  }
2687 
2688  auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2689  SDValue Result = DAG.getTargetJumpTable(JT->getIndex(), PtrVT, OpFlag);
2690  SDLoc DL(JT);
2691  Result = DAG.getNode(WrapperKind, DL, PtrVT, Result);

2764 
2765 void M68kTargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(SDValue Op,
2766  std::string &Constraint,
2767  std::vector<SDValue> &Ops,
2768  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2769  SDValue Result;
2770 
2771  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
2772  // Constant constraints
2773  switch (Constraint[0]) {
2774  case 'I':
2775  case 'J':
2776  case 'K':
2777  case 'L':
2778  case 'M':
2779  case 'N':
2780  case 'O':
2781  case 'P': {
2782  auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op);
2783  if (!C)
2784  return;
2785 
2786  int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
2787  switch (Constraint[0]) {
2788  case 'I': // constant integer in the range [1,8]
2789  if (Val > 0 && Val <= 8)
2790  break;
2791  return;
2792  case 'J': // constant signed 16-bit integer
2793  if (isInt<16>(Val))
2794  break;
2795  return;
2796  case 'K': // constant that is NOT in the range of [-0x80, 0x80)
2797  if (Val < -0x80 || Val >= 0x80)
2798  break;
2799  return;
2800  case 'L': // constant integer in the range [-8,-1]
2801  if (Val < 0 && Val >= -8)
2802  break;
2803  return;
2804  case 'M': // constant that is NOT in the range of [-0x100, 0x100]
2805  if (Val < -0x100 || Val >= 0x100)
2806  break;
2807  return;
2808  case 'N': // constant integer in the range [24,31]
2809  if (Val >= 24 && Val <= 31)
2810  break;
2811  return;
2812  case 'O': // constant integer 16
2813  if (Val == 16)
2814  break;
2815  return;
2816  case 'P': // constant integer in the range [8,15]
2817  if (Val >= 8 && Val <= 15)
2818  break;
2819  return;
2820  default:
2821  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled constant constraint");
2822  }
2823 
2824  Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(Op), Op.getValueType());
2825  break;
2826  }
2827  default:
2828  break;
2829  }
2830  }
2831 
2832  if (Constraint.size() == 2) {
2833  switch (Constraint[0]) {
2834  case 'C':
2835  // Constant constraints start with 'C'
2836  switch (Constraint[1]) {
2837  case '0':
2838  case 'i':
2839  case 'j': {
2840  auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op);
2841  if (!C)
2842  break;
2843 
2844  int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
2845  switch (Constraint[1]) {
2846  case '0': // constant integer 0
2847  if (!Val)
2848  break;
2849  return;
2850  case 'i': // constant integer
2851  break;
2852  case 'j': // integer constant that doesn't fit in 16 bits
2853  if (!isInt<16>(C->getSExtValue()))
2854  break;
2855  return;
2856  default:
2857  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled constant constraint");
2858  }
2859 
2860  Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(Op), Op.getValueType());
2861  break;
2862  }
2863  default:
2864  break;
2865  }
2866  break;
2867  default:
2868  break;
2869  }
2870  }
2871 
2872  if (Result.getNode()) {
2873  Ops.push_back(Result);
2874  return;
2875  }
2876 
2877  TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG);
2878 }

2924 // Return true if it is OK for this CMOV pseudo-opcode to be cascaded
2925 // together with other CMOV pseudo-opcodes into a single basic-block with
2926 // conditional jump around it.
2927 static bool isCMOVPseudo(MachineInstr &MI) {
2928  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2929  case M68k::CMOV8d:
2930  case M68k::CMOV16d:
2931  case M68k::CMOV32r:
2932  return true;
2933 
2934  default:
2935  return false;
2936  }
2937 }
2938 
2939 // The CCR operand of SelectItr might be missing a kill marker
2940 // because there were multiple uses of CCR, and ISel didn't know
2941 // which to mark. Figure out whether SelectItr should have had a
2942 // kill marker, and set it if it should. Returns the correct kill
2943 // marker value.
2944 static bool checkAndUpdateCCRKill(MachineBasicBlock::iterator SelectItr,
2945  MachineBasicBlock *BB,
2946  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) {
2947  // Scan forward through BB for a use/def of CCR.
2948  MachineBasicBlock::iterator miI(std::next(SelectItr));
2949  for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator miE = BB->end(); miI != miE; ++miI) {
2950  const MachineInstr &mi = *miI;
2951  if (mi.readsRegister(M68k::CCR))
2952  return false;
2953  if (mi.definesRegister(M68k::CCR))
2954  break; // Should have kill-flag - update below.
2955  }
2956 
2957  // If we hit the end of the block, check whether CCR is live into a
2958  // successor.
2959  if (miI == BB->end())
2960  for (const auto *SBB : BB->successors())
2961  if (SBB->isLiveIn(M68k::CCR))
2962  return false;
2963 
2964  // We found a def, or hit the end of the basic block and CCR wasn't live
2965  // out. SelectMI should have a kill flag on CCR.
2966  SelectItr->addRegisterKilled(M68k::CCR, TRI);
2967  return true;
2968 }

2970 MachineBasicBlock *
2971 M68kTargetLowering::EmitLoweredSelect(MachineInstr &MI,
2972  MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
2973  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
2974  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
2975 
2976  // To "insert" a SELECT_CC instruction, we actually have to insert the
2977  // diamond control-flow pattern. The incoming instruction knows the
2978  // destination vreg to set, the condition code register to branch on, the
2979  // true/false values to select between, and a branch opcode to use.
2980  const BasicBlock *BB = MBB->getBasicBlock();
2981  MachineFunction::iterator It = ++MBB->getIterator();
2982 
2983  // ThisMBB:
2984  // ...
2985  // TrueVal = ...
2986  // cmp ccX, r1, r2
2987  // bcc Copy1MBB
2988  // fallthrough --> Copy0MBB
2989  MachineBasicBlock *ThisMBB = MBB;
2990  MachineFunction *F = MBB->getParent();
2991 
2992  // This code lowers all pseudo-CMOV instructions. Generally it lowers these
2993  // as described above, by inserting a MBB, and then making a PHI at the join
2994  // point to select the true and false operands of the CMOV in the PHI.
2995  //
2996  // The code also handles two different cases of multiple CMOV opcodes
2997  // in a row.
2998  //
2999  // Case 1:
3000  // In this case, there are multiple CMOVs in a row, all which are based on
3001  // the same condition setting (or the exact opposite condition setting).
3002  // In this case we can lower all the CMOVs using a single inserted MBB, and
3003  // then make a number of PHIs at the join point to model the CMOVs. The only
3004  // trickiness here, is that in a case like:
3005  //
3006  // t2 = CMOV cond1 t1, f1
3007  // t3 = CMOV cond1 t2, f2
3008  //
3009  // when rewriting this into PHIs, we have to perform some renaming on the
3010  // temps since you cannot have a PHI operand refer to a PHI result earlier
3011  // in the same block. The "simple" but wrong lowering would be:
3012  //
3013  // t2 = PHI t1(BB1), f1(BB2)
3014  // t3 = PHI t2(BB1), f2(BB2)
3015  //
3016  // but clearly t2 is not defined in BB1, so that is incorrect. The proper
3017  // renaming is to note that on the path through BB1, t2 is really just a
3018  // copy of t1, and do that renaming, properly generating:
3019  //
3020  // t2 = PHI t1(BB1), f1(BB2)
3021  // t3 = PHI t1(BB1), f2(BB2)
3022  //
3023  // Case 2, we lower cascaded CMOVs such as
3024  //
3025  // (CMOV (CMOV F, T, cc1), T, cc2)
3026  //
3027  // to two successives branches.
3028  MachineInstr *CascadedCMOV = nullptr;
3029  MachineInstr *LastCMOV = &MI;
3030  M68k::CondCode CC = M68k::CondCode(MI.getOperand(3).getImm());
3031  M68k::CondCode OppCC = M68k::GetOppositeBranchCondition(CC);
3032  MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextMIIt =
3033  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI));
3034 
3035  // Check for case 1, where there are multiple CMOVs with the same condition
3036  // first. Of the two cases of multiple CMOV lowerings, case 1 reduces the
3037  // number of jumps the most.
3038 
3039  if (isCMOVPseudo(MI)) {
3040  // See if we have a string of CMOVS with the same condition.
3041  while (NextMIIt != MBB->end() && isCMOVPseudo(*NextMIIt) &&
3042  (NextMIIt->getOperand(3).getImm() == CC ||
3043  NextMIIt->getOperand(3).getImm() == OppCC)) {
3044  LastCMOV = &*NextMIIt;
3045  ++NextMIIt;
3046  }
3047  }
3048 
3049  // This checks for case 2, but only do this if we didn't already find
3050  // case 1, as indicated by LastCMOV == MI.
3051  if (LastCMOV == &MI && NextMIIt != MBB->end() &&
3052  NextMIIt->getOpcode() == MI.getOpcode() &&
3053  NextMIIt->getOperand(2).getReg() == MI.getOperand(2).getReg() &&
3054  NextMIIt->getOperand(1).getReg() == MI.getOperand(0).getReg() &&
3055  NextMIIt->getOperand(1).isKill()) {
3056  CascadedCMOV = &*NextMIIt;
3057  }
3058 
3059  MachineBasicBlock *Jcc1MBB = nullptr;
3060 
3061  // If we have a cascaded CMOV, we lower it to two successive branches to
3062  // the same block. CCR is used by both, so mark it as live in the second.
3063  if (CascadedCMOV) {
3064  Jcc1MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB);
3065  F->insert(It, Jcc1MBB);
3066  Jcc1MBB->addLiveIn(M68k::CCR);
3067  }
3068 
3069  MachineBasicBlock *Copy0MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB);
3070  MachineBasicBlock *SinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB);
3071  F->insert(It, Copy0MBB);
3072  F->insert(It, SinkMBB);
3073 
3074  // If the CCR register isn't dead in the terminator, then claim that it's
3075  // live into the sink and copy blocks.
3076  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
3077 
3078  MachineInstr *LastCCRSUser = CascadedCMOV ? CascadedCMOV : LastCMOV;
3079  if (!LastCCRSUser->killsRegister(M68k::CCR) &&
3080  !checkAndUpdateCCRKill(LastCCRSUser, MBB, TRI)) {
3081  Copy0MBB->addLiveIn(M68k::CCR);
3082  SinkMBB->addLiveIn(M68k::CCR);
3083  }
3084 
3085  // Transfer the remainder of MBB and its successor edges to SinkMBB.
3086  SinkMBB->splice(SinkMBB->begin(), MBB,
3087  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(LastCMOV)), MBB->end());
3088  SinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(MBB);
3089 
3090  // Add the true and fallthrough blocks as its successors.
3091  if (CascadedCMOV) {
3092  // The fallthrough block may be Jcc1MBB, if we have a cascaded CMOV.
3093  MBB->addSuccessor(Jcc1MBB);
3094 
3095  // In that case, Jcc1MBB will itself fallthrough the Copy0MBB, and
3096  // jump to the SinkMBB.
3097  Jcc1MBB->addSuccessor(Copy0MBB);
3098  Jcc1MBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
3099  } else {
3100  MBB->addSuccessor(Copy0MBB);
3101  }
3102 
3103  // The true block target of the first (or only) branch is always SinkMBB.
3104  MBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
3105 
3106  // Create the conditional branch instruction.
3107  unsigned Opc = M68k::GetCondBranchFromCond(CC);
3108  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(Opc)).addMBB(SinkMBB);
3109 
3110  if (CascadedCMOV) {
3111  unsigned Opc2 = M68k::GetCondBranchFromCond(
3112  (M68k::CondCode)CascadedCMOV->getOperand(3).getImm());
3113  BuildMI(Jcc1MBB, DL, TII->get(Opc2)).addMBB(SinkMBB);
3114  }
3115 
3116  // Copy0MBB:
3117  // %FalseValue = ...
3118  // # fallthrough to SinkMBB
3119  Copy0MBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
3120 
3121  // SinkMBB:
3122  // %Result = phi [ %FalseValue, Copy0MBB ], [ %TrueValue, ThisMBB ]
3123  // ...
3124  MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItBegin = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI);
3125  MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItEnd =
3126  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(LastCMOV));
3127  MachineBasicBlock::iterator SinkInsertionPoint = SinkMBB->begin();
3128  DenseMap<unsigned, std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>> RegRewriteTable;
3129  MachineInstrBuilder MIB;
3130 
3131  // As we are creating the PHIs, we have to be careful if there is more than
3132  // one. Later CMOVs may reference the results of earlier CMOVs, but later
3133  // PHIs have to reference the individual true/false inputs from earlier PHIs.
3134  // That also means that PHI construction must work forward from earlier to
3135  // later, and that the code must maintain a mapping from earlier PHI's
3136  // destination registers, and the registers that went into the PHI.
3137 
3138  for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIIt = MIItBegin; MIIt != MIItEnd; ++MIIt) {
3139  Register DestReg = MIIt->getOperand(0).getReg();
3140  Register Op1Reg = MIIt->getOperand(1).getReg();
3141  Register Op2Reg = MIIt->getOperand(2).getReg();
3142 
3143  // If this CMOV we are generating is the opposite condition from
3144  // the jump we generated, then we have to swap the operands for the
3145  // PHI that is going to be generated.
3146  if (MIIt->getOperand(3).getImm() == OppCC)
3147  std::swap(Op1Reg, Op2Reg);
3148 
3149  if (RegRewriteTable.find(Op1Reg) != RegRewriteTable.end())
3150  Op1Reg = RegRewriteTable[Op1Reg].first;
3151 
3152  if (RegRewriteTable.find(Op2Reg) != RegRewriteTable.end())
3153  Op2Reg = RegRewriteTable[Op2Reg].second;
3154 
3155  MIB =
3156  BuildMI(*SinkMBB, SinkInsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(M68k::PHI), DestReg)
3157  .addReg(Op1Reg)
3158  .addMBB(Copy0MBB)
3159  .addReg(Op2Reg)
3160  .addMBB(ThisMBB);
3161 
3162  // Add this PHI to the rewrite table.
3163  RegRewriteTable[DestReg] = std::make_pair(Op1Reg, Op2Reg);
3164  }
3165 
3166  // If we have a cascaded CMOV, the second Jcc provides the same incoming
3167  // value as the first Jcc (the True operand of the SELECT_CC/CMOV nodes).
3168  if (CascadedCMOV) {
3169  MIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg()).addMBB(Jcc1MBB);
3170  // Copy the PHI result to the register defined by the second CMOV.
3171  BuildMI(*SinkMBB, std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MIB.getInstr())),
3172  DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY),
3173  CascadedCMOV->getOperand(0).getReg())
3174  .addReg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
3175  CascadedCMOV->eraseFromParent();
3176  }
3177 
3178  // Now remove the CMOV(s).
3179  for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIIt = MIItBegin; MIIt != MIItEnd;)
3180  (MIIt++)->eraseFromParent();
3181 
3182  return SinkMBB;
3183 }

3221 // Lower dynamic stack allocation to _alloca call for Cygwin/Mingw targets.
3222 // Calls to _alloca are needed to probe the stack when allocating more than 4k
3223 // bytes in one go. Touching the stack at 4K increments is necessary to ensure
3224 // that the guard pages used by the OS virtual memory manager are allocated in
3225 // correct sequence.
3226 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(SDValue Op,
3227  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3228  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
3229  bool SplitStack = MF.shouldSplitStack();
3230 
3231  SDLoc DL(Op);
3232 
3233  // Get the inputs.
3234  SDNode *Node = Op.getNode();
3235  SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
3236  SDValue Size = Op.getOperand(1);
3237  unsigned Align = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getZExtValue();
3238  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3239 
3240  // Chain the dynamic stack allocation so that it doesn't modify the stack
3241  // pointer when other instructions are using the stack.
3242  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, 0, 0, DL);
3243 
3244  SDValue Result;
3245  if (SplitStack) {
3246  auto &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
3247  auto SPTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
3248  auto *ARClass = getRegClassFor(SPTy);
3249  Register Vreg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(ARClass);
3250  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Vreg, Size);
3251  Result = DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SEG_ALLOCA, DL, SPTy, Chain,
3252  DAG.getRegister(Vreg, SPTy));
3253  } else {
3254  auto &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
3255  Register SPReg = TLI.getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore();
3256  assert(SPReg && "Target cannot require DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC expansion and"
3257  " not tell us which reg is the stack pointer!");
3258 
3259  SDValue SP = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, SPReg, VT);
3260  Chain = SP.getValue(1);
3261  const TargetFrameLowering &TFI = *Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
3262  unsigned StackAlign = TFI.getStackAlignment();
3263  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, SP, Size); // Value
3264  if (Align > StackAlign)
3265  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Result,
3266  DAG.getConstant(-(uint64_t)Align, DL, VT));
3267  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, SPReg, Result); // Output chain
3268  }

3270  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, 0, 0, SDValue(), DL);
3271 
3272  SDValue Ops[2] = {Result, Chain};
3273  return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
3274 }

3276 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerShiftLeftParts(SDValue Op,
3277  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3278  SDLoc DL(Op);
3279  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
3280  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
3281  SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
3282  EVT VT = Lo.getValueType();
3283 
3284  // if Shamt - register size < 0: // Shamt < register size
3285  // Lo = Lo << Shamt
3286  // Hi = (Hi << Shamt) | ((Lo >>u 1) >>u (register size - 1 ^ Shamt))
3287  // else:
3288  // Lo = 0
3289  // Hi = Lo << (Shamt - register size)
3290 
3291  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
3292  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT);
3293  SDValue MinusRegisterSize = DAG.getConstant(-32, DL, VT);
3294  SDValue RegisterSizeMinus1 = DAG.getConstant(32 - 1, DL, VT);
3295  SDValue ShamtMinusRegisterSize =
3296  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Shamt, MinusRegisterSize);
3297  SDValue RegisterSizeMinus1Shamt =
3298  DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, RegisterSizeMinus1, Shamt);
3299 
3300  SDValue LoTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
3301  SDValue ShiftRight1Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, One);
3302  SDValue ShiftRightLo =
3303  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, ShiftRight1Lo, RegisterSizeMinus1Shamt);
3304  SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
3305  SDValue HiTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo);
3306  SDValue HiFalse = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, ShamtMinusRegisterSize);
3307 
3308  SDValue CC =
3309  DAG.getSetCC(DL, MVT::i8, ShamtMinusRegisterSize, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
3310 
3311  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, LoTrue, Zero);
3312  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, HiTrue, HiFalse);
3313 
3314  return DAG.getMergeValues({Lo, Hi}, DL);
3315 }

3317 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::LowerShiftRightParts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3318  bool IsSRA) const {
3319  SDLoc DL(Op);
3320  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
3321  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
3322  SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
3323  EVT VT = Lo.getValueType();
3324 
3325  // SRA expansion:
3326  // if Shamt - register size < 0: // Shamt < register size
3327  // Lo = (Lo >>u Shamt) | ((Hi << 1) << (register size - 1 ^ Shamt))
3328  // Hi = Hi >>s Shamt
3329  // else:
3330  // Lo = Hi >>s (Shamt - register size);
3331  // Hi = Hi >>s (register size - 1)
3332  //
3333  // SRL expansion:
3334  // if Shamt - register size < 0: // Shamt < register size
3335  // Lo = (Lo >>u Shamt) | ((Hi << 1) << (register size - 1 ^ Shamt))
3336  // Hi = Hi >>u Shamt
3337  // else:
3338  // Lo = Hi >>u (Shamt - register size);
3339  // Hi = 0;
3340 
3341  unsigned ShiftRightOp = IsSRA ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL;
3342 
3343  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
3344  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT);
3345  SDValue MinusRegisterSize = DAG.getConstant(-32, DL, VT);
3346  SDValue RegisterSizeMinus1 = DAG.getConstant(32 - 1, DL, VT);
3347  SDValue ShamtMinusRegisterSize =
3348  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Shamt, MinusRegisterSize);
3349  SDValue RegisterSizeMinus1Shamt =
3350  DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, RegisterSizeMinus1, Shamt);
3351 
3352  SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
3353  SDValue ShiftLeftHi1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, One);
3354  SDValue ShiftLeftHi =
3355  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi1, RegisterSizeMinus1Shamt);
3356  SDValue LoTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftRightLo, ShiftLeftHi);
3357  SDValue HiTrue = DAG.getNode(ShiftRightOp, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
3358  SDValue LoFalse =
3359  DAG.getNode(ShiftRightOp, DL, VT, Hi, ShamtMinusRegisterSize);
3360  SDValue HiFalse =
3361  IsSRA ? DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Hi, RegisterSizeMinus1) : Zero;
3362 
3363  SDValue CC =
3364  DAG.getSetCC(DL, MVT::i8, ShamtMinusRegisterSize, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
3365 
3366  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, LoTrue, LoFalse);
3367  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, HiTrue, HiFalse);
3368 
3369  return DAG.getMergeValues({Lo, Hi}, DL);
3370 }

3376 static SDValue getSETCC(M68k::CondCode Cond, SDValue CCR, const SDLoc &dl,
3377  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
3378  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SETCC, dl, MVT::i8,
3379  DAG.getConstant(Cond, dl, MVT::i8), CCR);
3380 }
3381 // When legalizing carry, we create carries via add X, -1
3382 // If that comes from an actual carry, via setcc, we use the
3383 // carry directly.
3384 static SDValue combineCarryThroughADD(SDValue CCR) {
3385  if (CCR.getOpcode() == M68kISD::ADD) {
3386  if (isAllOnesConstant(CCR.getOperand(1))) {
3387  SDValue Carry = CCR.getOperand(0);
3388  while (Carry.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE ||
3389  Carry.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND ||
3390  Carry.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
3391  Carry.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND ||
3392  (Carry.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
3393  isOneConstant(Carry.getOperand(1))))
3394  Carry = Carry.getOperand(0);
3395  if (Carry.getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC ||
3396  Carry.getOpcode() == M68kISD::SETCC_CARRY) {
3397  if (Carry.getConstantOperandVal(0) == M68k::COND_CS)
3398  return Carry.getOperand(1);
3399  }
3400  }
3401  }
3402 
3403  return SDValue();
3404 }
3405 
3406 /// Optimize a CCR definition used according to the condition code \p CC into
3407 /// a simpler CCR value, potentially returning a new \p CC and replacing uses
3408 /// of chain values.
3409 static SDValue combineSetCCCCR(SDValue CCR, M68k::CondCode &CC,
3410  SelectionDAG &DAG,
3411  const M68kSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3412  if (CC == M68k::COND_CS)
3413  if (SDValue Flags = combineCarryThroughADD(CCR))
3414  return Flags;
3415 
3416  return SDValue();
3417 }
3418 
3419 // Optimize RES = M68kISD::SETCC CONDCODE, CCR_INPUT
3420 static SDValue combineM68kSetCC(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3421  const M68kSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3422  SDLoc DL(N);
3423  M68k::CondCode CC = M68k::CondCode(N->getConstantOperandVal(0));
3424  SDValue CCR = N->getOperand(1);
3425 
3426  // Try to simplify the CCR and condition code operands.
3427  if (SDValue Flags = combineSetCCCCR(CCR, CC, DAG, Subtarget))
3428  return getSETCC(CC, Flags, DL, DAG);
3429 
3430  return SDValue();
3431 }
3432 static SDValue combineM68kBrCond(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3433  const M68kSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3434  SDLoc DL(N);
3435  M68k::CondCode CC = M68k::CondCode(N->getConstantOperandVal(2));
3436  SDValue CCR = N->getOperand(3);
3437 
3438  // Try to simplify the CCR and condition code operands.
3439  // Make sure to not keep references to operands, as combineSetCCCCR can
3440  // RAUW them under us.
3441  if (SDValue Flags = combineSetCCCCR(CCR, CC, DAG, Subtarget)) {
3442  SDValue Cond = DAG.getConstant(CC, DL, MVT::i8);
3443  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::BRCOND, DL, N->getVTList(), N->getOperand(0),
3444  N->getOperand(1), Cond, Flags);
3445  }
3446 
3447  return SDValue();
3448 }

3450 static SDValue combineSUBX(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
3451  if (SDValue Flags = combineCarryThroughADD(N->getOperand(2))) {
3452  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
3453  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::i32);
3454  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::SUBX, SDLoc(N), VTs, N->getOperand(0),
3455  N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3456  }
3457 
3458  return SDValue();
3459 }
3460 
3461 // Optimize RES, CCR = M68kISD::ADDX LHS, RHS, CCR
3462 static SDValue combineADDX(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3463  TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) {
3464  if (SDValue Flags = combineCarryThroughADD(N->getOperand(2))) {
3465  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
3466  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::i32);
3467  return DAG.getNode(M68kISD::ADDX, SDLoc(N), VTs, N->getOperand(0),
3468  N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3469  }
3470 
3471  return SDValue();
3472 }

3474 SDValue M68kTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
3475  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
3476  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
3477  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
3478  case M68kISD::SUBX:
3479  return combineSUBX(N, DAG);
3480  case M68kISD::ADDX:
3481  return combineADDX(N, DAG, DCI);
3482  case M68kISD::SETCC:
3483  return combineM68kSetCC(N, DAG, Subtarget);
3484  case M68kISD::BRCOND:
3485  return combineM68kBrCond(N, DAG, Subtarget);
3486  }
3487 
3488  return SDValue();
3489 }
